4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 Preheat outdoor grill or charcoal grill to 325°F and lightly oil the grates.
4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 Place the turkey tenderloins on the grill and cook 10 to 12 ½ minutes then flip.
4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 Continue to cook until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165° F (approximately 10 to 12 ½ additional minutes). Use a meat thermometer to confirm internal temperature.
4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 While turkey tenderloins are cooking, prepare the Southwest salad.
4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 Place the chopped Southwest salad mix, Pico, corn, black beans, cheese and tortilla strips in a mixing bowl. Add the dressing and gently toss until thoroughly coated.
4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 Place the mixed salad on a large platter. Remove the tenderloins from the grill and allow to rest for 5 minutes. Slice into ¼ slices and place on top of the mixed salad.
4f4e59a4-1d20-40a6-a9d6-572fb124cb51 Serve immediately.
9b52ddf6-1da0-4b35-a0b3-78dee43abcec Place a pizza stone on lowest rack in oven and preheat oven to 475°F. Alternatively use an inverted large heavy baking sheet.
9b52ddf6-1da0-4b35-a0b3-78dee43abcec Lightly dust a pizza peel with flour. Working quickly, dust pizza dough with flour and stretch gently into a rustic oval shape. Prick dough all over with a fork and transfer dough to the pizza stone or baking sheet in the oven. Bake until just cooked through, approximately 15 minutes, checking periodically for bubbles in the dough. Use a fork to break any large bubbles as the dough bakes.
9b52ddf6-1da0-4b35-a0b3-78dee43abcec Let pizza flatbread cool slightly, then top with meatballs, mozzarella, tomatoes, and roasted red peppers. Drizzle generously with basil pesto and serve.
9b52ddf6-1da0-4b35-a0b3-78dee43abcec For the basil pesto, combine the garlic, basil, and pine nuts in a food processor and process until finely chopped. With the motor running, drizzle in the oil. Transfer the mixture to a small bowl and stir in Parmesan cheese. Season with Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper. If making ahead of time, top pesto with a thin layer of extra virgin olive oil to prevent browning and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature and stir before serving. Notes: You can find premade pizza dough at many grocery stores, but another fantastic option to grab one from your local pizzeria! Pizza dough straight from the refrigerator is difficult to stretch. Let dough rest at room temperature for at least 10 minutes before stretching. They are usually the same price as the ones in the supermarket and taste way better. You can also grill your pizza dough! Preheat grill to medium-high heat and oil grill grates. Carefully lay dough on grill and let cook about 2 to 4 minutes, until grill marks appear and the dough easily releases from the grill. Use tongs to flip dough over and cook on other side another 2-3 minutes, until dough is completely cooked through. Remove pizza from grill.
2eef8475-6030-4ef6-8de0-21ec49e527eb Slice tomatoes into wedges (for a medium-sized tomato, slice into 6 wedges).
2eef8475-6030-4ef6-8de0-21ec49e527eb Assemble each skewer with a meatball and piece of mozzarella in-between two tomato wedges. Serve with Basil Pesto.
2eef8475-6030-4ef6-8de0-21ec49e527eb For the Basil Pesto, combine the garlic, basil, and pine nuts in a food processor and process until finely chopped. With the motor running, drizzle in the oil. Transfer the mixture to a small bowl and stir in Parmesan cheese. Season with Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper. If making ahead of time, top pesto with a thin layer of extra virgin olive oil to prevent browning and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature and stir before serving.
6a568903-3468-4784-986e-6fdbd990e84c Place a pizza stone on lowest rack in oven and preheat oven to 475°F. Alternatively use an inverted large heavy baking sheet.
6a568903-3468-4784-986e-6fdbd990e84c Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add spinach, season with Kosher salt, and cook until wilted.
6a568903-3468-4784-986e-6fdbd990e84c Lightly dust a pizza peel with flour. Working quickly, dust pizza dough with flour and stretch gently into a thin circle shape. Spread pizza sauce in a thin, even layer across dough. Scatter spinach, meatball halves, and ricotta on pizza. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
6a568903-3468-4784-986e-6fdbd990e84c Transfer pizza to the pizza stone or baking sheet in oven and bake pizza in oven until dough is just cooked through, approximately 15 minutes.
6a568903-3468-4784-986e-6fdbd990e84c Remove from oven, let cool for 2-3 minutes, then slice and serve! Notes: You can find premade pizza dough at many grocery stores, but another fantastic option to grab one from your local pizzeria! Pizza dough straight from the refrigerator is difficult to stretch. Let dough rest at room temperature for at least 10 minutes before stretching. They are usually the same price as the ones in the supermarket and taste way better.
3dc9cb76-2078-48ee-b322-37bb6bf93ebe In a skillet, heat the butter and 12 sage leaves over medium heat and season generously with Kosher salt. Stir the butter constantly, especially as it begins to foam and sizzle. Continually watch butter as it cooks, removing from heat once the butter turns golden brown and smells nutty. Immediately transfer brown sage butter to a bowl to stop the cooking process. Let cool until its cool to the touch.
3dc9cb76-2078-48ee-b322-37bb6bf93ebe Preheat oven to 325°F. Remove turkey from packaging and follow the listed prep directions on back of package. Pat turkey dry and place on the rack of your roasting pan. Stuff the cavity of your turkey with the onion, remaining 4 sage leaves, and season generously with Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper. Drizzle and smear half of the browned butter all over the surface of the turkey and under the skin. Season turkey with freshly ground black pepper.
3dc9cb76-2078-48ee-b322-37bb6bf93ebe Cook turkey according to package directions, until the internal temperature reaches 165°F at the thickest part of the turkey. Approximately every 45 minutes, baste the turkey. To baste, remove turkey from oven and gently tilt the pan to scoop up the pan liquids and drizzle them on top of the turkey.
3dc9cb76-2078-48ee-b322-37bb6bf93ebe Remove turkey from oven, cover with aluminum foil, and let rest for 20-30 minutes before slicing and serving. Drizzle turkey and roasted root vegetables with reserved sage brown butter.
3dc9cb76-2078-48ee-b322-37bb6bf93ebe For the Roasted Root Vegetables, place vegetables on a large baking sheet in a single layer (or divide among multiple baking sheets as needed). Toss with olive oil and season generously with Kosher salt. Roast in oven during the last 45 minutes of turkey cooking. Drizzle with sage brown butter.
f2bba645-1d74-46b9-89a0-4517880a9d2a Bring Turkey Injection to boil. Let cool and then inject bird. Cover bird with olive oil. Use favorite dry rub (we recommend Greek seasoning). Cover exterior of bird. Put an ice pack on the breast side of the turkey to make it cooler so that it cooks a little slower and doesnt dry out
f2bba645-1d74-46b9-89a0-4517880a9d2a Bring smoker to 250-320°F. Put bird on. Remove when bird reaches 165°F in breast and 170°F in thigh. Let rest 30 minutes and enjoy!
2420dfde-dda4-4361-89d4-db882597ba83 In warm water add salt and sugar, stir and allow to fully dissolve. Add remaining brine ingredients and finally ice to fully cool. Once cold, place turkey in brine and fully submerge. Store in refrigerator for 12-24 hours.
2420dfde-dda4-4361-89d4-db882597ba83 When turkey has finished brining, preheat oven to 350°F. Remove turkey from the brine, rinse, and pat dry. Place in roasting pan.
2420dfde-dda4-4361-89d4-db882597ba83 In a small bowl, mix butter with Herbs de Provence, salt and pepper, then rub under skin. Liberally season cavity with salt and pepper. I would add some aromatics to the cavity (onion, lemon, hearty herb like thyme).
2420dfde-dda4-4361-89d4-db882597ba83 Bake at until golden brown and internal temperature is 165°F in the thickest area of the breast. Rotate turkey after roasting for approximately 1 hour and baste with juices in pan. Cover loosely with foil if turkey browns too quickly.
2420dfde-dda4-4361-89d4-db882597ba83 Allow the turkey to rest covered for 15-20 minutes before carving.
f59ab909-8595-4b15-a9da-a86f6a62b505 Preheat oven to 350°F. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and spread all over the outside of the turkey breast. Place on rack inside roasting pan and cook according to package directions.
f59ab909-8595-4b15-a9da-a86f6a62b505 Meanwhile, combine apple juice, maple syrup, and bourbon in a small saucepan. Season with Kosher salt and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Lower heat to maintain a simmer, cooking to reduce the mixture by half. Add butter and continue to reduce for about 10 minutes. Glaze will continue to thicken as it cools.
f59ab909-8595-4b15-a9da-a86f6a62b505 After 1 hour of cooking turkey breast, and in twenty minute intervals following this, brush turkey breast with the maple bourbon glaze. Remove turkey breast from oven once it reaches 160°F. Cover with aluminum foil and let rest for 10 minutes (temperature will continue to rise as it rests). Slice turkey and serve with extra glaze and roasted root vegetables.
f59ab909-8595-4b15-a9da-a86f6a62b505 For the roasted root vegetables, place vegetables on a large baking sheet. Toss with olive oil and season generously with Kosher salt. Roast in oven during the last 45 minutes of turkey cooking. Drizzle with extra glaze, if desired.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 Set your smoker to 265ºF.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 Rinse the turkey breast under cold water and pat dry.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 Mix together the salt and pepper and season the turkey breast.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 Release the skin on both breasts and place sage leaves under the skin.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 Make sure you have a water bath in your smoker to prevent the turkey from becoming dry. Smoke the turkey until golden brown - around 2.5 hours and a temperature reading of ~130ºF.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 At this point wrap your turkey in a double layer of foil and pour the melted butter over the breasts. Put back in the smoker until your meat thermometer reads 160ºF. This should take about another hour of cooking. Let it rest.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 For the cranberry relish, heat olive oil in a pan over a medium/high heat. Add diced red onion and pine nuts and cook until golden brown. Add chopped cranberries and celery and cook for another minute or two. Add smoked paprika, balsamic, orange juice and orange zest. Cook until liquids have reduced by half.
bc3bd35e-75fc-49b6-8086-280a874813a0 Remove from heat and stir in chopped parsley, jalapeño and season with salt and pepper. Can be served hot or cold.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a In warm water add salt and sugar, stir and allow to fully dissolve. Add remaining brine ingredients and finally ice to fully cool. Once cold, place turkey in brine and fully submerge. Store in refrigerator for 12-24 hours.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a When turkey has finished brining, preheat oven to 350°F. Remove turkey from the brine, rinse, and pat dry. Place in roasting pan.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a In a bowl mix fennel, garlic, leeks, apples, thyme, orange with 1 tablespoon of olive oil, and generous amount of salt and pepper. Stuff seasoned aromatics into turkey cavity.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a Brush turkey with remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a Add wine to the bottom of roasting pan.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a Bake until golden brown and internal temperature is 165°F in the thickest area of the breast. Rotate turkey after roasting for approximately 1 hour and baste with juices in pan. Cover loosely with foil if turkey browns too quickly.
45f34abc-97bf-4aa4-9586-04b28d47bd3a Allow the turkey to rest covered for 15-20 minutes before carving.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb Preheat the oven to 375°F. Start by roasting the garlic first. Slice the tops off the garlic heads and drizzle them with olive oil. Wrap the heads in foil and stick them in the oven for 40 minutes or so while you make everything else!
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb Heat a skillet over medium heat and add the olive oil. Stir in the onions and garlic, cooking until softened and translucent, about 5 minutes. Stir in the fresh parsley. Remove from the heat and let cool slightly.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb In a bowl, combine the ground turkey, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, milk, egg, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil, parsley, garlic and pepper. Use your hands to bring the mixture together, until just combined and the ingredients are evenly distributed. Form the mixture into mini meatloaves about 1 inch in thickness and 2 inches in length.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb Heat the same skillet back up over medium heat and add another tablespoon of olive oil. Add the meatloaves in the skillet and brown on both sides, about 3 to 4 minutes per side.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb Stir together the ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar in a bowl. Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons on top of each meatloaf. Place the skillet in the oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the center of the meatloaves reach 165°F. When finished, sprinkle with fresh parsley.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb While the meatloaves are in the oven, make your cauliflower mash. Cut the head of cauliflower into florets. Place them in a large pot or saucepan and cover them with water, just about an inch past the top of the cauliflower. Bring the mixture to a boil and cook until tender, about 10 minutes or so. Drain the cauliflower, reserving about 1/4 cup of the liquid.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb Add the cauliflower to a food processor and blend until pureed. Stream in the cooking liquid and the melted butter, along with a pinch of salt and pepper. By this time, the garlic cloves should be roasted. Squeeze them from the paper into the cauliflower puree. Puree again to combine. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if needed.
65c4b12b-27e8-4c97-9fcd-0cd71ff552bb Serve the meatloaves and cauliflower mash with a veggie of your choice! We love a green bean or brussel sprouts. Enjoy!
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Preheat the oven to 400°F.
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Heat a skillet over medium heat and add the olive oil. Add in the onions, peppers and garlic with a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until the onions soften, about 5 minutes. Stir in the spinach until it wilts. Turn off the heat and let the mixture cool slightly.
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Carefully slice the turkey tenderloins lengthwise. We like to slice it twice to open it up, so we have a lot of space to work with. I start at the bottom of the tenderloin (about 1/4 inch from the bottom) and slice it lengthwise, then continue to cut again and open up the turkey. You want to have a flat surface to work on. Once the tenderloins are sliced open, I take a meat tenderizer and pound them out to make them one even layer.
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Add half of the onion/pepper mixture to the top of each tenderloin leaving an inch or so around the edges so you can roll it up. Sprinkle each with half of the cheddar cheese.
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Tightly roll up the tenderloin and tie it together with kitchen twine if needed.
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Place the tenderloins on the baking sheet and roast for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the inside is cooked and reads about 160°F. Let the turkey rest for 10 minutes before slicing.
30143873-6c93-4e39-a5ae-4a0be4af3dad Serve with the lime black bean salad.
5ef94b2f-7415-4a94-8cf9-2b16c57cfd42 Remove seasoned turkey breast cutlets from skillet kit and slice into long thin strips. Cut open the sauté sauce packet. Set aside.
5ef94b2f-7415-4a94-8cf9-2b16c57cfd42 Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add bell peppers, onions and salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 8 minutes until the vegetables have softened.
5ef94b2f-7415-4a94-8cf9-2b16c57cfd42 Transfer cooked peppers and onions to a large bowl, cover with aluminum foil and set aside.
5ef94b2f-7415-4a94-8cf9-2b16c57cfd42 In the same skillet, add remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add sliced turkey strips and cook for 8 minutes, until turkey is cooked through.
5ef94b2f-7415-4a94-8cf9-2b16c57cfd42 Add the softened peppers and onions to the skillet, pour in the sauté sauce and toss to coat. Cook everything for 1-2 more minutes until everything has warmed through and the sauce is bubbling.
5ef94b2f-7415-4a94-8cf9-2b16c57cfd42 Serve immediately in warm corn tortillas for tacos, over rice for burrito bowls or in lettuce for lettuce cups.
44860c13-eb39-4697-93c9-63ad096ab4ca Heat olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onions and sauté for 5 minutes until softened.
44860c13-eb39-4697-93c9-63ad096ab4ca Add ground turkey and 1 teaspoon salt. Mix together and break up the meat using a spatula. Cook for 8-10 minutes, until the meat has browned and fully cooked through.
44860c13-eb39-4697-93c9-63ad096ab4ca Transfer cooked ground turkey and onions to a large slow cooker. Add chicken broth, diced tomatoes, black beans, pinto beans, corn, the remaining 1 tablespoon salt, chili powder, ground cumin, smoked paprika and dried oregano.
44860c13-eb39-4697-93c9-63ad096ab4ca Mix together until fully combined. Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours. The longer it cooks, the thicker and more concentrated the flavor of the broth will be.
44860c13-eb39-4697-93c9-63ad096ab4ca Mix in lime juice, cilantro (if desired) and cream cheese (if you want the soup a little creamy).
44860c13-eb39-4697-93c9-63ad096ab4ca Serve and top with tortilla strips and shredded cheese.
c4a98adf-c46d-49cc-a3d0-de8a7b96fbf5 Heat olive oil in large sauce pan, with deep sides, to medium high heat. When hot, add turkey cutlets. Cook for 3-4 minutes on each side. Remove from pan and let rest for 5 minutes on cutting board.
c4a98adf-c46d-49cc-a3d0-de8a7b96fbf5 Slice turkey into thin strips, and cut in half. Add back to skillet, along with skillet sauce packet, fire roasted tomatoes, and pasta. Stir to combine, then add box of chicken broth and black pepper.
c4a98adf-c46d-49cc-a3d0-de8a7b96fbf5 Cover and cook for 8-10 minutes, until pasta is al dente. Remove from heat, and stir in spinach, vinegar, and cheese. Let sit for 5 minutes so spinach wilts. Taste, and add salt as needed. This will depend on the amount of sodium in your broth. Scoop into bowls and finish with extra cheese and fresh basil. The fresh basil adds so much freshness, don't leave it out!
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea To prepare the seasoning, add softened butter, chipotle peppers, chopped rosemary leaves, salt, black pepper, oregano, orange zest, lime zest, and minced garlic in a food processor. Pulse until mixture comes together and resembles a paste.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea To prepare the turkey, preheat oven to 450°F. Remove thawed turkey from the packaging and take out the turkey neck and bag of giblets stuffed inside. Discard or keep to use in a different recipe. Pat turkey dry with a handful of paper towels or a large kitchen towel until completely dry. Place turkey on a baking sheet and set aside.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Fill the bottom of the roasting pan with the juice of the zested orange, the juiced orange quarters and 2 cups of turkey stock.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Fill the turkey cavity with the onion halves, the sprig of rosemary and the orange quarters. Tie the turkey legs together with kitchen twine to help the turkey cook evenly and for a beautiful presentation.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Carefully push your fingers under the skin of the turkey breast all the way to the back of the turkey to help separate the skin. Be careful not to tear the skin.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Spread half of the compound butter under the skin and the remaining half all over the outside of the turkey. Secure the edges of the skin with some toothpicks so it doesnt ride up completely while the bird is roasting.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea To roast the turkey, place turkey breast side up in the roasting pan and insert an in-oven meat thermometer deep inside the breast of the bird. Make sure its not touching a bone. Set the in-oven meat thermometer temperature to 165°F. Place the turkey in the preheated oven and roast for 25 minutes to crisp the skin.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Remove turkey from oven, lower the heat to 350°F, loosely cover the breast with a tent of aluminum foil and return to the oven. Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until the temperature of the meat reaches 165°F.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Carefully remove from oven and check the temperature of the bird in different places to make sure everything is at least 170°F. If there are spots that are under, leave the thermometer in that spot and return it to the oven to roast until it reaches 170°F.
f6e22b25-cd0f-4fb4-a31d-6ed8fea090ea Carefully transfer the turkey to large cutting board and rest for 30 minutes. Slice and serve.
0087242f-fda3-4d6d-a48c-12072516e5bf Place oven rack in the bottom third of the oven. Heat oven to 450°F.
0087242f-fda3-4d6d-a48c-12072516e5bf Pat the skin of the turkey breast dry with paper towels and on roasting rack. Set aside. In a small bowl, combine garlic, butter, mustard, herbs, and salt. Mix until well combined, forming a paste.
0087242f-fda3-4d6d-a48c-12072516e5bf Carefully loosen the skin from the turkey breast and rub the herb mixture on the meat under the skin. Pull the skin back to cover the turkey breast. Rub any remaining herb mixture over the skin
0087242f-fda3-4d6d-a48c-12072516e5bf Place the turkey breast in the oven and lower the oven heat to 350°F . Roast the turkey breast for 1 hour, turning halfway. If the breast begins to brown too quickly, form a tent with foil. Check the internal temperature of the turkey breast at the 1-hour point, followed by every 10 minutes until it reaches an internal temperature of 165°F at the thickest part of the breast.
0087242f-fda3-4d6d-a48c-12072516e5bf Remove the turkey breast from the oven and let rest for 10 to 15 minutes before carving.
0087242f-fda3-4d6d-a48c-12072516e5bf If you have enough pan drippings, make gravy: Remove the rack, and place roasting pan directly over a burner set on high heat. Add 1 tablespoon unbleached all-purpose flour to pan, and whisk for 2 minutes, scraping up the pan drippings and incorporating all of the pan juices into the flour. Add 1/2 cup water, and continue whisking until a smooth gravy forms, about 2 minutes. Transfer to a gravy boat, and serve with turkey.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Brine the turkey for 6-8 hours in water, 4 tbsp of Cajun seasoning, and 4 tbsp of salt. Make sure that the brine fully covers the turkey.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Preheat the oven to 400 °F. Take the innards out of the turkey.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Take out the turkey and pat it dry with paper towels. Place half of the orange and lemon onto a roasting pan. Place the turkey breast-side up in the roasting pan.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Pour olive oil over the turkey and rub it in. Rub the ghee into the turkey. Make sure to rub the insides too. Sprinkle (heavily) the cajun seasoning over the turkey and rub it in.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Place the garlic, onion, half of the thyme, half of the orange and half of the lemon into the turkey.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Make sure the legs are still looped together. Tuck the wings under the bird.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Cover the turkey with foil and roast it for 20 minutes. Try to let as little steam as possible escape the pan.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Pour the broth into the pan. Add the other half of the thyme to the pan. Roast the bird for 40 minutes.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc Reduce the oven temperature to 350 degrees. Take off the foil cook for 2 more hours, basting occasionally with pan juices about every 30 minutes.
aae8b81b-ac14-4a55-b738-7089b7d45fdc After the bird is done, put it on a platter and cover it with foil for about 20-30 minutes. Bonus tip: If your turkey starts to look dry when it's being served, pour some olive oil on it to give it a little life. I had to do this when I hosted my Friendsgiving and it livened it right up!
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Preheat oven to 400°F.
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Next, prepare vegetables. Cut carrots in half hot dog-style and then again hamburger-style so that you quarter them. Place them on baking sheet.
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Slice a medium-sized onion and add that to the baking sheet. Next, slice both ends off of 2 bulbs of garlic, keeping them in their casing and place those on the baking sheet as well.
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Drizzle veggies with olive oil and season with salt and pepper and toss so that everything is coated.
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Roast vegetables at 400°F for 25 minutes. Then, remove and toss. Drizzle on honey and balsamic vinegar and toss again. Make sure to flip garlic heads over.
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Place back in the oven and roast for another 20 minutes at 400°F.
e6900ac7-0da2-4cf3-9d73-46ee3c3ddce7 Remove from oven and let cool for 5-10 minutes. Then, carefully squeeze garlic cloves out of the bulbs and toss with roasted vegetables.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 First, prepare sous vide water bath by filling a 14 quart pot (or larger) with water. Youll want enough water to cover your turkey when submerged.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Set the sous vide to 165°F and bring water to temperature.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Next, remove thawed turkey breast from the refrigerator and remove gravy packet. Use paper towel to remove any excess moisture from the turkey breast and set aside.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Place dried thyme, rosemary, oregano, brown sugar, garlic powder, salt, pepper, chili powder, and paprika into a small bowl and mix until combined.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Next, sprinkle the dry rub over the turkey breast and use your hands to rub it into every part of the turkey until all meat is generously covered.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Let the turkey sit with the dry rub for at least 20 minutes or up to 2 hours (for a more intense flavor, let sit for longer).
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Next, sear the turkey by placing 3-4 tablespoons of butter into a large cast-iron skillet.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 When butter is fragrant, place turkey skin side down onto the cast-iron skillet. Let cook for 3-4 minutes on each side.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Remove from the cast iron skillet and place turkey breast into a large food saver bag. We used an 11-inch food saver roll, and it fit an 8 lb turkey perfectly.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Make an herb bundle with the fresh rosemary, fresh thyme, and fresh sage and then add it to the bag along with white wine.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Use your food saver machine to remove as much air out of the bag as possible and then seal. Double bag your turkey by placing it into another 11-inch bag to prevent tears and leaking. Remove air and seal.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Place the turkey into the sous vide water bath and clip it into place so it doesnt move. Make sure the turkey is submerged in water. If its not, we suggest placing a pot on top of it to hold it under water.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Let the turkey breast cook in the sous vide at 165°F for at least 12 hours or up to 24 hours.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Once your turkey is fully cooked, remove it from the bag and set it aside.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Then, preheat oven to 400°F
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Discard herbs from the bag, but pour the excess liquid from the plastic bag through a sieve and into s bowl and set aside.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Check the internal temperature of the turkey and make sure it is between 163°F and 165°F.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Then, melt 3-4 tablespoons of butter in a large cast iron skillet.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 When butter is melted and very hot, place the turkey breast into the pan, skin-side down. Sear for 3-4 minutes or until browned, and then repeat on the other side.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Turn heat off and pour sauce over the turkey breast.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Next, place the cast iron skillet and turkey into the oven and roast at 400°F for 20 minutes, basting the turkey with the sauce every 5 minutes.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Once golden brown, remove turkey from oven and let rest for 10-15 minutes before slicing and serving.
b3fcb8a8-5a4b-470a-b914-d6c1ddb64815 Transfer sauce from cast iron skillet and thicken as desired, or serve as-is on top of the sliced turkey breast.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Make sure your oven is clean and free of debris and spills. A dirty oven will produce smoke at the high temperatures required for this recipe.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Place your oven rack at the second to last position. Placing it in the lowest position may risk burning your bird!
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Preheat oven to 475°F.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Remove the giblets and neck from the turkey. If there is a plastic truss holding the legs together, remove it. We will not truss the turkey for this recipe.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Rinse the turkey inside and out and drain water. Then, pat dry with paper towels.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Put about one inch of water or broth in the bottom of your roasting pan. This will make sure that the oven does not produce excessive smoke during this high heat roast. Please dont skip this step!
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Place turkey on roasting pan. Make sure you are placing it on a rack, not on the bottom of the pan, which should be full of water or broth to prevent smoking.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Rub turkey with avocado oil, then sprinkle with salt, pepper, thyme and garlic powder.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Make aluminum foil covers for each drumstick to prevent burning.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Roast for the following, turning the bird 180°F about halfway through your cook time. My 14 lb bird took about 1.5 hours.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 The turkey is done when your instant read thermometer reads 165°F in the thickest part of BOTH the breast and the thigh.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 For the glaze, melt the butter in a small saucepan over medium-high heat.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Stir in bourbon and maple syrup.
83d8f486-605a-4b17-bbcc-7dc405a4fba8 Once glaze comes to a boil, lower heat to low-medium heat and allow to thicken for about 10 minutes.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Preheat outdoor grill or charcoal grill to 350°F and lightly oil the grates.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 To prepare the stuffed tenderloins, add bacon to a sauté pan over medium heat. Cook the bacon until it becomes crispy, reserving the bacon grease. Remove cooked bacon from the pan and set aside until needed.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Add the garlic, onions, roasted red peppers and roasted corn. Cook until the onions are softened and lightly browned. Remove and allow to cool to room temperature. Once cooled, add the bacon and cheddar cheese and mix thoroughly.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 While cooling, butterfly the turkey tenderloins then use a meat tenderizer to pound them out to an equal thickness.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Add half the stuffing to each of the tenderloins, leaving an inch or so in order to roll it up. Once rolled, tie with butcher's twine from end to end.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Place the stuffed turkey tenderloin on the grill and cook 10 to 12 ½ minutes then flip.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Continue to cook until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F (approximately 10 to 12 ½ additional minutes). Use a meat thermometer to confirm internal temperature.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Once cooked, remove from the grill. Allow to rest for 5 minutes then slice into 1 slices.
3b472105-a056-4fe6-9638-c06e1762cc05 Place on a platter and serve immediately.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Preheat oven to 400°F. Place a large baking sheet in the oven while it is preheating.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Thinly slice 4 garlic cloves.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c In a spice grinder, puree the other 2 garlic cloves, fennel seed, red pepper flakes and salt.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Pat tenderloins dry with paper towels.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Make small slits all over the turkey tenderloins and stuff garlic slices inside.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Rub spice mixture over the tenderloins.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c In a large bowl, mix together rutabaga, carrots, oil, salt and pepper.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Take hot baking sheet out of oven and pour vegetables into a single layer on the baking sheet. Place turkey tenderloins on top.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Cook until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165¬F using a meat thermometer and vegetables are tender.
d47919d7-55f9-464c-aeb2-85ed9397e52c Place turkey onto a cutting board and let rest for 10 minutes before slicing.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Place salt, brown sugar, garlic powder and dried rosemary in a small bowl. Work with fingers until incorporated. Place turkey on a wire rack set inside a rimmed baking sheet. Sprinkle and pat brine all over outside and inside of turkey, nudging some into crevices. Chill bird, uncovered, for at least 12 hours and up to 2 days.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Remove turkey from rack and rinse baking dish. Line with 3 layers of aluminum foil and set rack back inside. Place turkey, breast side up, on rack and tuck wings underneath. Allow turkey to sit at room temperature for 2-3 hours.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Preheat oven to 450°F. Loosen skin on turkey breasts and spread 2 tablespoons of butter underneath skin atop both breasts. Smear outside of turkey with another 2 tablespoons of butter.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Tie legs with kitchen twine and transfer turkey to oven. Pour 1 cup water into baking sheet and roast, rotating pan after 15 minutes, until skin is golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Meanwhile, heat 4 remaining tablespoons of butter, vinegar, honey, Worcestershire sauce, rosemary, garlic, and orange zest over medium heat until bubbling and slightly thickened, about 7 minutes. Reduce heat to low to keep warm.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Reduce oven temperature to 300°F and continue to roast turkey, brushing glaze every 30 minutes and adding an additional 1/2 cup of water to the baking sheet to retain liquid. Continue until the thickest part of breast reads 150 degrees on an instant-read thermometer, about 60-90 minutes longer when skin reaches brown, crisp and shiny look.
c1751334-f3f1-4227-9000-90f2949a0210 Transfer turkey to a cutting board and allow to rest 30 minutes before carving.
3fb4c2be-0e8d-4ca3-8898-7b5aea908e39 Follow package directions of the Parmesan Garlic Meatballs.
3fb4c2be-0e8d-4ca3-8898-7b5aea908e39 While the meatballs are cooking prepare the tomato cream sauce.
3fb4c2be-0e8d-4ca3-8898-7b5aea908e39 Place marinara and cream in a small sauce pot. Stir together then bring to a rapid boil. Reduce to a simmer and add in the ¼ cup of shredded parmesan. Keep warm over a low temperature.
3fb4c2be-0e8d-4ca3-8898-7b5aea908e39 Using a meat thermometer, check to make sure the meatballs reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F. Once the proper temperature has been reached, remove from oven.
3fb4c2be-0e8d-4ca3-8898-7b5aea908e39 On a platter, pour the heated sauce on the bottom. Randomly place the meatballs over the top of the sauce.
3fb4c2be-0e8d-4ca3-8898-7b5aea908e39 Garnish with chopped fresh basil and 2 tablespoons. of shredded parmesan cheese, serve immediately.
b72bed66-ab8e-403f-a71b-6a379434f78d In a large saute pan, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil over medium heat. Swirl to coat pan, then add in squash. Stir the squash pieces so they are coated with oil and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt. Shake the pan so squash spreads out in an even layer and let cook, without stirring, so that they brown a bit on one side (several minutes).
b72bed66-ab8e-403f-a71b-6a379434f78d Stir and spread the pieces out again and let cook without stirring so more sides brown. Cover, and cook about 6 minutes, until the squash is soft, but holds its shape (This will depend on the size you cut your squash so try one to test). Once done, remove from heat and pour into a bowl.
b72bed66-ab8e-403f-a71b-6a379434f78d Heat remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil of oil over medium-high heat using the same pan. When it's very hot, place the brussels sprouts cut side down in the oil, sprinkling with 1 teaspoon salt. Turn the heat to medium, and sear on one side until nicely browned, about 3 minutes.
b72bed66-ab8e-403f-a71b-6a379434f78d Turn the brussels sprouts over and cook on the other side until nicely browned and tender, three to five minutes. Some of the leaves can be charred dark brown or black.
b72bed66-ab8e-403f-a71b-6a379434f78d Turn heat down to low and add the squash back to the pan, along with the pecan mix. Stir in the glaze and cook for a few minutes, coating all ingredients and warming through.
9bd78997-0ebd-4371-9f96-1a96e020685b Preheat an 8- to 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat for 2-3 minutes.
9bd78997-0ebd-4371-9f96-1a96e020685b Add 2 teaspoons extra virgin olive oil.
9bd78997-0ebd-4371-9f96-1a96e020685b Add turkey to pan, and cook until browned and crumbly. Ensure that turkey reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
9bd78997-0ebd-4371-9f96-1a96e020685b Stir in simmer sauce, let cook for 3 minutes.
9bd78997-0ebd-4371-9f96-1a96e020685b Reduce heat to low.
9bd78997-0ebd-4371-9f96-1a96e020685b Build your taco with your favorite toppings, and enjoy!
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Preheat an 8-10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat for 2 - 3 minutes.
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Add 2 teaspoons extra virgin olive oil.
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Add turkey to pan and cook until browned and crumbly. Ensure that turkey reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Stir in simmer sauce, salt, ancho, coriander and chipotle.
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Reduce heat to low.
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Cook 3 minutes.
43c22fd7-c2ee-4f1f-8f44-10e40f54c43f Warm tortillas and assemble tacos with meat, onions, cilantro, a dash of hot sauce and a squeeze of lime.
e4d9ff1d-f9a2-4c88-94ae-a7dfb555d7a2 Arrange rack in middle of oven; preheat to 400°F. Mix garlic, cumin, oil, paprika, pepper, oregano, 2 teaspoons salt, and finely grated zest from lemon in a medium bowl.
e4d9ff1d-f9a2-4c88-94ae-a7dfb555d7a2 Cut lemon in half and squeeze out juice into spice mixture. Rub the cut lemons all over the turkey, and any remaining juice. Place lemons in cavity of turkey.
e4d9ff1d-f9a2-4c88-94ae-a7dfb555d7a2 Place turkey in a roasting pan, or aluminum sheet pan with parchment underneath, breast side facing up. From both edges of cavity, loosen skin from breasts, being careful not to tear skin. Using your fingers, gently spread 3/4 of spice mixture under skin (reserve remaining spice mixture), then season turkey skin all over with remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
e4d9ff1d-f9a2-4c88-94ae-a7dfb555d7a2 Roast turkey 10 minutes, then turn heat down to 375°F. Continue roasting, basting with remaining spice mixture and pan juices every 20 minutes, until thickest part of breast is pierced with instant-read thermometer and reads 155-165°F.
e4d9ff1d-f9a2-4c88-94ae-a7dfb555d7a2 Transfer turkey to a cutting board and let rest 15 minutes, where its temperature will continue to rise to 170°F.
e4d9ff1d-f9a2-4c88-94ae-a7dfb555d7a2 Purée cilantro, jalapeños, garlic, oil, lime juice, and salt in a blender until combined. Add mayonnaise and purée until well blended. Transfer to a small bowl, cover, and chill until ready to use.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Preheat and 8- to 10-inch nonstick skillet on medium heat for 2-3 minutes.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Add 2 teaspoons extra virgin olive oil.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Add turkey and cook until browned and crumbly. Ensure that turkey reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Reduce heat to low.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Add spice packet and water; cook 3 minutes.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Warm tortillas.
856ca9ab-876b-4c71-9621-2fd2dc026694 Pile on the taco meat, mango salsa, cilantro and hot sauce, and enjoy!
eb08227e-f67a-4f02-8c87-520ee1659f71 Preheat oven to 400°F.
eb08227e-f67a-4f02-8c87-520ee1659f71 Line a sheet tray with foil, coat lightly with olive oil.
eb08227e-f67a-4f02-8c87-520ee1659f71 Toss veggies with olive oil, salt and pepper.
eb08227e-f67a-4f02-8c87-520ee1659f71 Place turkey tenderloin in the center of the tray and veggies.
eb08227e-f67a-4f02-8c87-520ee1659f71 Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until the turkey is 170°F and the edges of the veggies are lightly browned.
eb08227e-f67a-4f02-8c87-520ee1659f71 Squeeze fresh lemon juice on the veggies, add parsley, serve and enjoy!
177b53c1-98bf-40ac-af1c-09fc30809c7c Preheat oven to 400°F.
177b53c1-98bf-40ac-af1c-09fc30809c7c Line a sheet tray with foil, coat lightly with olive oil.
177b53c1-98bf-40ac-af1c-09fc30809c7c Toss veggies with olive oil, adobo, salt and pepper.
177b53c1-98bf-40ac-af1c-09fc30809c7c Place turkey in middle of sheet tray and add veggies around the turkey.
177b53c1-98bf-40ac-af1c-09fc30809c7c Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until the turkey reaches an internal temperature of 170°F using a meat thermometer and the edges of the veggies are lightly browned.
177b53c1-98bf-40ac-af1c-09fc30809c7c Serve with chopped cilantro, your favorite shredded cheese, and enjoy!
c4409e16-80c3-493c-af28-045591cdfb23 Preheat oven to 400°F.
c4409e16-80c3-493c-af28-045591cdfb23 Line a sheet tray with foil and coat with a thin layer of olive oil.
c4409e16-80c3-493c-af28-045591cdfb23 Toss veggies with olive oil, salt and pepper.
c4409e16-80c3-493c-af28-045591cdfb23 Place turkey in the center of the tray and add veggies around turkey.
c4409e16-80c3-493c-af28-045591cdfb23 Bake 30-35 minutes or until turkey is cooked to 170°F and the edges of the veggies are lightly browned.
c4409e16-80c3-493c-af28-045591cdfb23 Sprinkle with cheese, serve and enjoy!
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a non-stick skillet over medium high heat.
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc Add all turkey cutlets to the pan. Sear and brown one side, approximately 2-3 minutes. Flip cutlets over and cook an additional 2-3 minutes.
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc Pour contents of sauce packet over the top of the turkey cutlets and stir.
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc Continue to simmer cutlets and sauce until the cutlets reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F as measured by a meat thermometer (approximately additional 3-4 minutes).
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc Heat the rice per package instructions.
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc For the garlic broccoli, place the sesame oil in a saute pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and broccoli and cook until softened and heated throughout, approximately 5-8 minutes.
9cee42ab-4141-4d92-9ebc-b9dee41036dc Plate turkey and sauce, garnishing with green onions and toasted sesame. Serve with rice topped with garlic broccoli.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a non-stick skillet over medium high heat.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Add all turkey cutlets to the pan. Sear and brown one side, approximately 2-3 minutes. Flip cutlets over and cook an additional 2-3 minutes.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Pour contents of sauce packet over the top of the turkey cutlets and stir.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Continue to simmer cutlets and sauce until the cutlets reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F as measured by a meat thermometer (approximately additional 3-4 minutes).
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 For the creamy pasta: cook pasta according to package directions.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 To make the sauce, place the butter in a sauce pan over medium heat. Once melted add the garlic and cook until lightly brown, approximately 2 minutes.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Add the heavy cream and bring to a boil. Once it comes to a boil reduce heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese. Cook until melted.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Season with salt and pepper, then stir in the sun-dried tomatoes and the spinach. Cook until the spinach wilts, approximately 5 additional minutes.
3c44064e-409b-4ff4-af2a-81cb736e78c6 Mix sauce with the cooked pasta. Serve pasta, turkey and sauce with garlic bread.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a non-stick skillet over medium high heat.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Add all turkey cutlets to the pan. Sear and brown one side, approximately 2-3 minutes. Flip cutlets over and cook an additional 2-3 minutes.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Pour contents of sauce packet over the top of the turkey cutlets and stir.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Continue to simmer cutlets and sauce until the cutlets reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F as measured by a meat thermometer (approximately additional 3-4 minutes).
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Heat the rice per package directions.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 For the stir fry veggies: heat the toasted sesame oil in a sauté pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and vegetables and cook until softened and heated throughout, approximately 5-8 minutes.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Pour rice into a bowl and top with cooked veggies.
16e3fec6-3fe3-4a4a-9557-fd6621492019 Garnish turkey and sauce with green onions. Serve with rice and veggies.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Prior to cooking the turkey cutlets, prepare the hash.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place a sheet pan in the oven to heat.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Cut potatoes, peppers and onion into bite size pieces. Place in a mixing bowl and add the olive oil, salt, pepper and cumin. Toss until coated.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Place vegetables on the heated sheet pan and cook for 35 minutes until potatoes are cooked and the vegetables are roasted and browned.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e While the hash is cooking, heat 2 tablespoons oil in a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Add all turkey cutlets to the pan. Sear and brown one side, approximately 2-3 minutes. Flip cutlets over and cook an additional 2-3 minutes.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Pour contents of sauce packet over the top of the turkey cutlets and stir.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Continue to simmer cutlets and sauce until the cutlets reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F as measured by a meat thermometer (approximately additional 3-4 minutes).
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Remove roasted vegetables from oven. To serve, plate roasted vegetables, place turkey and sauce on top.
ff9dce54-810f-4e3b-bef2-620bec20868e Garnish with grated Cotija cheese or queso fresco and pico de gallo.
ec2f0a20-edc3-485b-9102-4d2afc08dddb Preheat large saucepan over medium high heat. When hot, add shallots and sauté for 4-5 minutes until translucent. Add garlic, ginger, 1/2 tablespoon curry powder and 1 teaspoon salt. Stir and combine. Then add bell pepper and continue to cook for 3 minutes.
ec2f0a20-edc3-485b-9102-4d2afc08dddb Push vegetables to one side of pan. Add turkey and break up using a wooden spoon or firm spatula. Once cooked through and no pink remains, add remaining 1 tablespoon curry powder and 1 teaspoon kosher salt. Stir thoroughly.
ec2f0a20-edc3-485b-9102-4d2afc08dddb Then add coconut milk tamari. Take out a few tablespoons of the cooking liquid and whisk it with the arrowroot or tapioca starch. Add this mixture back to pan and stir.
ec2f0a20-edc3-485b-9102-4d2afc08dddb Add in zucchini and spinach. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in lime juice. Serve over warm rice and garnish with red pepper flakes and cilantro.
1050b270-ed16-48d9-8be5-8b236d0ef076 Preheat oven to 350°F.
1050b270-ed16-48d9-8be5-8b236d0ef076 Add olive oil to cast iron skillet and set to medium high heat. When hot, add turkey tenderloins and garlic cloves, and cook for 4 minutes on each side, to sear. Remove from heat and place in oven. Cook until interior of meat reaches 150-155°F. Remove from oven and place turkey on cutting board to rest, covered with tented foil. Set garlic aside, to use for cauliflower.
1050b270-ed16-48d9-8be5-8b236d0ef076 Meanwhile, add cauliflower, milk, bay leaves, thyme, salt, and ground pepper to a large saucepan. Bring to a simmer, and cover. Cook for 8-10 minutes, until cauliflower is easily pierced with a fork and tender. Remove bay leaves, and thyme.
1050b270-ed16-48d9-8be5-8b236d0ef076 Using a slotted spoon, add cauliflower and roasted garlic to a blender. Then add 1 cup of warm milk. Blend for 30 seconds, adding additional milk by 1/4 cup according to how thick or thin youd like the puree to be, until completely smooth. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.
1050b270-ed16-48d9-8be5-8b236d0ef076 Slice turkey into 1/2 inch slices, and plate over the cauliflower puree. Garnish with additional olive oil and pomegranate seeds.
fc9b78a6-a701-4068-a682-c4a34794baa9 Cook pasta according to package directions. Take a large bowl and place it underneath your colander when you drain the pasta. You are going to save 1 cup of the pasta water. This is important because it has starch in it and will help the sauce thicken.
fc9b78a6-a701-4068-a682-c4a34794baa9 In a large skillet pan, with deep sides, heat olive oil over medium high heat. Once hot, add turkey cutlets. Cook for 5 minutes on each side. Remove from pan and let rest for a few minutes until slicing into thin strips.
fc9b78a6-a701-4068-a682-c4a34794baa9 Add pasta to skillet, then turkey, beans, skillet packet, salsa, and sour cream. Stir to fully combine. Add 3/4 cup pasta water, and cook on low heat, stirring. Add up to 1/4 cup more pasta water if you'd like to make even creamier. Stir in lime juice and cilantro.
fc9b78a6-a701-4068-a682-c4a34794baa9 Add cheese and cover, cooking until all melted. Then serve with additional cilantro if you like!
6c68835a-afd3-4715-9474-e584995f365e For the Tenderloin, follow package instructions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Bake in pan for approximately 50 to 60 minutes. Cook until internal temperature of the meat reaches 165°F.
6c68835a-afd3-4715-9474-e584995f365e For the Pesto, using a food processor, blend together the arugula or fresh basil, spinach, garlic and almonds and pulse until coarsely chopped. With the food processor running, slowly pour in the olive oil into the bowl, through the feed tube and blend until smooth, or to your desired consistency.
6c68835a-afd3-4715-9474-e584995f365e Add in the Parmesan chunks and pulse again until well combined. Taste and season with salt. Mix one more time.
6c68835a-afd3-4715-9474-e584995f365e To serve, slice and serve over mashed potatoes, or with a salad or roasted or steamed vegetables. Serve with homemade pesto on top. Enjoy!
add9ae1e-3228-4c9d-a62c-553731869db7 Preheat the oven to 400°F. Brush the peppers (inside and outside) with the olive oil and sprinkle with the salt, pepper and garlic powder. Place the peppers on a baking sheet and roast for 15 to 20 minutes.
add9ae1e-3228-4c9d-a62c-553731869db7 While the peppers are roasting, make the turkey taco meat. Heat a large skillet over medium heat and add the olive oil. Add the diced peppers, shallot and garlic with a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring often, until softened, about 5 minutes.
add9ae1e-3228-4c9d-a62c-553731869db7 Add in the ground turkey, breaking it apart with a wooden spoon. Season it with the cumin, paprika, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Stir well, salt and pepper. Stir well, continuing to break apart the meat into small crumbles. Cook until the turkey has browned.
add9ae1e-3228-4c9d-a62c-553731869db7 Add the water and flour to a shaker bottle and shake for 30 seconds. Pour the mixture into the tacos, stirring well and cooking for another 5 to 6 minutes, until saucy.
add9ae1e-3228-4c9d-a62c-553731869db7 Remove the peppers from the oven. Fill the peppers with the turkey taco mixture.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df Preheat oven to 400°F.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df In a high-power blender, combine roasted peppers, garlic, basil, 2 tablespoons of olive oil, cashews, and water. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Blend the mixture on high until well blended and smooth. Set aside.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df Combine the zucchini, yellow squash, and onions in a 9x9 casserole dish (or similar size). Season vegetables with salt and pepper, and toss to combine. Set aside.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df In a non-stick skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the meatballs to the skillet and quickly sear on all sides, about 3-4 minutes total.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df Transfer the meatballs to the casserole dish and pour the red pepper sauce over the meatballs and the vegetables.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df Bake 25-35 or until the meatballs are fully cooked and the vegetables are tender. Meatballs are fully cooked when the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
3c24e92b-6f24-410a-8ce2-42ccaf71b9df Garnish with fresh chopped parsley and feta, if desired. Serve over cooked brown rice or cauliflower mash for a low carb option.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Preheat your oven to 350°F.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Bring a pot of water to boil and cook egg noodles according to package directions.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Place meatballs in oven safe baking dish and bake for 20-25 minutes, following package instructions. Meatballs are fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 In a large skillet over medium high heat, add olive oil and heat for 1-2 minutes. Add onion and mushrooms, sauté for 3-4 minutes until they begin to get fragrant. Add garlic, sauté for another 30 seconds, do not allow to brown.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Add butter to onions and mushrooms in pan, and melt, stirring vigorously. Once melted, add flour and continue to stir vigorously until the flour has absorbed the butter and formed a paste.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Add beef broth and whisk vigorously to remove lumps on high heat, allowing to boil for 2-3 minutes until it begins to thicken.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Turn burner off and whisk in sour cream and mushroom soup.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Stir until mixture is thoroughly incorporated.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Season with salt and pepper to your taste.
43a2f749-ecc1-4d3c-afdf-c6fec93a6522 Serve over egg noodles, top with meatballs.
af6562c8-41ae-4072-9cb5-69d97aec6aad Combine the skewer ingredients and set aside in refrigerator for at least an hour up to 24 hours.
af6562c8-41ae-4072-9cb5-69d97aec6aad Mix the jalapeño yogurt ingredients in a blender or food processor and blend until smooth. Set aside.
af6562c8-41ae-4072-9cb5-69d97aec6aad Skewer the turkey and alternate with the mushrooms. Pack them tight on the skewers.
af6562c8-41ae-4072-9cb5-69d97aec6aad Preheat grill to high heat.
af6562c8-41ae-4072-9cb5-69d97aec6aad Grill on high heat for about 10-15 minutes until browned and cooked through. Turkey is fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
af6562c8-41ae-4072-9cb5-69d97aec6aad Fill a bowl with rice and add cucumber, mint, and chiles. Top with skewers and drizzle on the yogurt.
94f91a98-fda5-457d-898d-887be195801e Heat a large sauté pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Add vegetable oil. Once hot add the Fajita seasoning and the turkey breast cutlets. Cook for 5 minutes, then add onions and peppers to the pan.
94f91a98-fda5-457d-898d-887be195801e Cook until the fajita strips reach a minimum internal temperature of 165 °F and the onions and peppers are soft and slightly browned (approximately 5 additional minutes).
94f91a98-fda5-457d-898d-887be195801e While the turkey is cooking, place the spring mix, dressing, tortilla strips and pico de gallo into a mixing bowl and gently toss.
94f91a98-fda5-457d-898d-887be195801e Place tossed salad on a large platter and top with cooked turkey and sautéed onions and peppers.
94f91a98-fda5-457d-898d-887be195801e Place guacamole into separate bowl and serve on the side.
94f91a98-fda5-457d-898d-887be195801e Serve your favorite salsa as well for an additional topping.
e54063ab-05e0-408e-8487-1a2213427c2a Heat a large sauté pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Add vegetable oil. Once hot add the turkey breast tenderloins. Cook for 5 minutes, then add onions, peppers and garlic to the pan.
e54063ab-05e0-408e-8487-1a2213427c2a Add the white wine to deglaze the pan, making sure to scrape the brown bits of turkey.
e54063ab-05e0-408e-8487-1a2213427c2a Add the diced tomatoes, chicken broth and oregano, allow to simmer for 20 minutes. Add the fresh basil and cook until the strips reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F.
e54063ab-05e0-408e-8487-1a2213427c2a Serve with mashed potatoes, polenta or rice.
90123d5f-49ad-4b10-9ae4-4d3295452de7 Cook pasta according to package.
90123d5f-49ad-4b10-9ae4-4d3295452de7 While pasta is cooking, sear your meatballs in a cooking pan over medium high heat. Add one cup of spaghetti sauce and continue to simmer until meatballs are cooked thoroughly, roughly 5-7 minutes. Meatballs are fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
90123d5f-49ad-4b10-9ae4-4d3295452de7 Place your spaghetti in a large bowl, add spaghetti sauce, grated parmesan cheese and mozzarella cheese. Mix until combined.
90123d5f-49ad-4b10-9ae4-4d3295452de7 Spray a 12 cup muffin tin with cooking spray. Divide spaghetti into the 12 baking cups. Create a small "hole" for your meatballs. If your meatballs are large, cut in half and add to the top of your spaghetti bites with some extra sauce. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
90123d5f-49ad-4b10-9ae4-4d3295452de7 Bake at 375°F for about 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and melted.
aa640049-86f9-4c28-922b-bbac26e53803 Baked Sweet Potato Fries: Preheat oven to 450¬F and line baking sheet with parchment paper. Peel sweet potatoes and slice into matchsticks, roughly the same size. Place in a large bowl and toss with olive oil and salt. Bake in the oven for 20 minutes on the parchment paper lined cookie sheet, tossing once halfway through to crisp up both sides.
aa640049-86f9-4c28-922b-bbac26e53803 Lemon Meringue Dipping Sauce: While the fries are baking mix together the mayo, garlic, lemon juice, lemon zest, and a pinch of salt.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad Preheat oven to 375°F.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad In a small bowl combine lemon pepper, oregano, and chili powder.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad Drizzle each turkey tenderloin with one tablespoon of olive oil and then season generously with spice mixture and salt.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad Arrange the seasoned turkey tenderloin on an aluminum foil lined baking sheet with place lemon slices, as desired.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad Roast for 40 minutes lightly covered with aluminum foil.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad Roast for an additional 15-20 minutes uncovered until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
4455b693-b5f1-45d2-8dd5-3543338b5cad Allow the turkey tenderloins to rest for 10 minutes. Use a sharp knife to slice and chop the tenderloins into 1/2-inch cubes.
647ee0e0-fe40-46d2-85b5-3528d9b922e5 Preheat oven to 350°F.
647ee0e0-fe40-46d2-85b5-3528d9b922e5 Sprinkle the paprika and oregano on all sides of the tenderloins, then place on foil or a parchment-lined baking sheet. Drizzle with the olive oil, as evenly as possible.
647ee0e0-fe40-46d2-85b5-3528d9b922e5 Roast at 350°F for 30-35 minutes or until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
647ee0e0-fe40-46d2-85b5-3528d9b922e5 Remove from the oven and let rest for 5-10 minutes before slicing.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Brine turkey breast in cool water and kosher salt for 4 6 hours (can also go as long as overnight).
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 To brine, place thawed turkey breast in a large bowl. Set aside.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Mix 8 cups of cool water with 1/4 cup kosher salt. Stir till dissolved.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Pour salt/water mixture over turkey breast until turkey breast is covered. Cover and place in refrigerator until ready to cook.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 When ready to cook, take turkey breast out of the brine. Discard brine.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Pat turkey dry with paper towels and remove and discard skin. Season generously with salt and pepper.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Pour apple cider and bullion in the bottom of Instant Pot, place steaming rack inside, and put seasoned turkey breast on top.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Lock lid, select the Meat function, and set timer for 45 minutes.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Quick release value after the timer beeps and remove the turkey breast from the cooker. Place on a foil-lined cookie sheet and brush barbecue sauce on the meat side of the breast.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Broil turkey breast for 5 6 minutes (watching carefully to prevent charring). Turkey is fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
6312f59c-92cc-4989-8e85-235534c41907 Shred breast after cooking and place on a platter. Serve with additional barbecue sauce on the side.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Balsamic Tomato Salad: In a small mixing bowl, combine the halved grape tomatoes, balsamic vinegar, and some freshly squeezed lime juice. Set aside.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Sriracha Mayo: In a small bowl, combine either avocado oil, Sriracha, sea salt, fresh lime juice, and unsweetened almond milk and stir to combine. You can set this aside as well.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Turkey Burgers: Grab about 1/2 cup of ground turkey and form into patties. Try to make the patties as evenly sized as possible so they cook evenly and are done at the same time.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Season both sides of the patties with a mixture of sea salt, ground black pepper, and garlic powder.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and add a little olive oil.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Add the patties, being careful not to overcrowd them, and cook about 5-6 minutes per side, until golden brown on both sizes and the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc To the same skillet, add the quartered red onion and cook on all sides until golden brown and tender, about 3-4 minutes per side. Then remove from the heat.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc To make the zucchini noodles, heat olive oil over medium-high heat and add the spiralized zucchini noodles, sea salt, and ground black pepper, and toss to coat.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc Cook until the noodles are just tender, about 6-8 minutes, tossing frequently.
0fa32eb9-9ac4-4d28-8510-0f6f6ad364fc To make the fried egg, add a little olive oil to a small skillet and heat over low heat. Add the egg and season with a little sea salt and ground black pepper.
eeff8d0d-34de-46a3-8a49-c25498606811 Remove turkey tenderloins from package. Rinse under warm water and set on paper towels, drying thoroughly. Set turkey tenderloins aside.
eeff8d0d-34de-46a3-8a49-c25498606811 In a small bowl, mix together minced garlic, basil, and ground pepper. Rub over turkey tenderloins until well coated on each side. Insert one clove into each of the ends and another one in the middle. Place into a gallon-sized resealable plastic bag (or place into a shallow glass pan).
eeff8d0d-34de-46a3-8a49-c25498606811 In a medium-sized bowl, blend vegetable oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, and brown sugar. Pour over turkey tenderloins and seal bag (or pour over in shallow pan). Turn to coat. Place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
eeff8d0d-34de-46a3-8a49-c25498606811 Preheat grill for high heat.
eeff8d0d-34de-46a3-8a49-c25498606811 Lightly oil grill grate with non-stick spray. Place turkey tenderloins on grill (discard marinade).
eeff8d0d-34de-46a3-8a49-c25498606811 Close lid and grill turkey tenderloins about 15 minutes on each side (depending on thickness), or until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Slice the onions and bell peppers and thread the vegetables onto the skewers.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Cut the tenderloins into 2 inch pieces and thread the turkey pieces onto the skewers.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Reserve the extra marinade from the marinated turkey breast tenderloins and brush over the vegetable skewers.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Set the grill temperature to medium high and allow the grill pan to heat thoroughly before placing your turkey skewers on the pan.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Allow the turkey skewers to sear nicely and take on nice grill marks before flipping them over. Grill for about 10 minutes per side.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Add a layer of foil to make a tent to keep the heat in place this will allow the juices of the turkey to redistribute throughout the turkey kabob.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Grill the vegetable skewers along side the turkey skewers. Turkey is fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
55b71956-dec6-446f-bb1f-54ad5a724e0d Serve the marinated grilled turkey kabobs with the grilled vegetable skewers on a platter with steamed rice or plate them individually, removing from the skewers.
358a5f23-80da-48a0-9b89-585f85e7e42b Heat grill to medium high heat.
358a5f23-80da-48a0-9b89-585f85e7e42b Season turkey breast cutlet strips with fajita seasoning.
358a5f23-80da-48a0-9b89-585f85e7e42b Thread bell peppers, onions and turkey breast cutlet strips onto skewers, alternating the meat and vegetables. For smaller cut pieces of turkey, thread one end of the meat, make a loop, and thread the other end to double it up.
358a5f23-80da-48a0-9b89-585f85e7e42b Oil the grill grates with vegetable oil before placing skewers on grill.
358a5f23-80da-48a0-9b89-585f85e7e42b Grill the kabobs for 2-3 minutes per side, covering while cooking. Cook until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
28fcdb67-2204-4820-894a-cac7b929f094 To prepare the guacamole, Place the avocado into a medium bowl and roughly mash with a fork. Stir in the onions, cilantro, and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
28fcdb67-2204-4820-894a-cac7b929f094 To prepare the Pico De Gallo, in a medium bowl, stir together the tomatoes, onions, cilantro, garlic, and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
28fcdb67-2204-4820-894a-cac7b929f094 For the Turkey Patties, prepare an outdoor grill on medium-high heat.
28fcdb67-2204-4820-894a-cac7b929f094 Place the turkey patties on the grill and cook for 3 minutes, covered. Flip and continue to cook, covered, for 3-4 minutes more or until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
28fcdb67-2204-4820-894a-cac7b929f094 Serve each turkey patty on a hamburger bun topped with guacamole.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 Preheat the grill on medium-high heat.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 In a bowl, combine ground turkey, taco seasoning, diced chili peppers, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly so that peppers are evenly distributed. Form into 4 patties.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 Pat each side of the turkey patties with bread crumbs.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 Grill turkey patties for about 8 minutes per side, cooking until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 While turkey patties are grilling, prepare your guacamole.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 Mash the avocados in a bowl with a fork or a pastry cutter, until desired the consistency is achieved. Add diced tomato, cumin, lime juice, salt and pepper to taste, set aside.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 Top burgers with pepper jack cheese during the last minute of grilling.
295980c3-118e-4636-a48d-d1de2c51eed3 To assemble, top each burger with guacamole and salsa.
cb7e09c1-c104-4bb3-af3d-229d3b56bb2e Prepare turkey burgers according to package directions. Cook until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
cb7e09c1-c104-4bb3-af3d-229d3b56bb2e Meanwhile, whisk together the mayo, garlic, herbs, lemon juice and zest. Season mixture with salt and pepper to taste.
cb7e09c1-c104-4bb3-af3d-229d3b56bb2e Arrange turkey burgers on buns, spread with a dollop of aioli, top with lettuce and tomato as desired.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d In a large skillet, cook the bacon over moderately high heat until crisp. Drain on paper towels and break each strip in half.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d Sprinkle ground turkey with kosher salt and pepper. Mix gently until well combined.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d Form into four 4-ounce burger patties.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat with olive oil. Add the patties and cook for 4 minutes, until golden brown and firm when pressed.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d Flip the burgers and cook for an additional 3 to 4 minutes or until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer. Top with a slice of cheese and let cheese melt for 1 minute.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d Set aside and allow to rest.
368ab6a2-a17a-4a0a-b49c-c75cbb91159d Spread mayonnaise on the cut sides of the buns; set the burgers on the bottoms and top with the bacon and roasted poblano and toppings of your choice.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Spray a grill pan or grill with cooking spray and heat over medium high heat.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Once hot, place the turkey patties on the grill.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd While the turkey patties cook, slice the baguette so you have a top and a bottom.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Cook the turkey patties for 6-7 minutes per side turning once and check temperature. Cook until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165¬F using a meat thermometer.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Remove from heat and rest for 3-5 minutes. Slice in half.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Drizzle a generous portion of Sriracha mayonnaise onto the bottom bun.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Place the patty halves onto the bottom bun in a single layer.
ab34f7e0-3fbe-4dd1-bdaf-92d96612d2bd Top with plenty of pickled vegetables, sliced jalapenos, fresh cilantro and the top bun. Serve immediately.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Preheat your grill and grill the turkey burgers for 4-5 minutes per side as per the package directions.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Cook until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Heat the oil over medium heat in a medium sauté pan. Add the minced onion, grated ginger, diced apple and sauté until golden.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Add the remaining ingredients to the saucepan and cook until the cranberries pop, about 10 mins. Remove from the heat and cool.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f The chutney can be stored in the refrigerator for several days.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Trim excess leaves and ends off of the Brussels sprouts.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Finely shred in a food processor, on a mandolin or with a sharp knife.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Combine the shredded Brussels sprouts, cranberries, toasted pecans, orange zest.
e68a046f-036e-4818-b750-4a94dbe80c9f Whisk together the honey, whole grain mustard, mayonnaise, orange juice, plain yogurt, apple cider vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
d429305e-39a5-459f-ac7a-89f050e75479 Combine chickpeas, lemon juice, garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt, tahini, 6 tablespoons olive oil and water.
d429305e-39a5-459f-ac7a-89f050e75479 In a food processor, puree chickpea mixture until smooth and creamy to create hummus.
d429305e-39a5-459f-ac7a-89f050e75479 In a non-stick skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat.
d429305e-39a5-459f-ac7a-89f050e75479 Add ground turkey to the skillet and season with the remaining teaspoon salt and pumpkin spice. Cook, stirring until brown and fragrant and turkey is cooked to 165° F, about 5-6 minutes.
d429305e-39a5-459f-ac7a-89f050e75479 Spread the hummus on a large flat plate or platter. Top with turkey mixture and garnish with pine nuts. Note: To toast pine nuts, bake for 5 minutes at 375° F on a baking sheet.
d429305e-39a5-459f-ac7a-89f050e75479 Serve with pita or pita chips and garnish with parsley or cilantro, if desired
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Heat a skillet over medium-high heat.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Add a tablespoon of oil and the garlic to the skillet. Cook, stirring until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Stir in tomatoes and their juices, along with Italian seasoning.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Bring the mixture in skillet to a boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer gently. Stir occasionally, until sauce has thickened but is still chunky, about 20 minutes.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Season the sauce with salt and pepper to taste and keep warm.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e While sauce simmers, pat turkey cutlets dry with a paper towel and season with a pinch of salt.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Heat the remaining tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Add the turkey cutlets to the skillet and cook for 6 minutes on one side. Flip the cutlets and cook for an additional 3 minutes, or until an internal temperature reaches 165°F, measured by a meat thermometer.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Spoon the warm tomato sauce over each cutlet. Excess sauce can be served with pasta as a side dish.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Sprinkle with mozzarella. Cover skillet and cook until cheese melts, about 3 minutes.
a6b8ca16-9bbd-413f-9cd3-1a1001c03e6e Garnish with basil.
5f7d6051-313a-42b5-a1d1-9a67e058b3cf In a small bowl, whisk together yogurt, Sriracha sauce, lime juice and water, then set aside.
5f7d6051-313a-42b5-a1d1-9a67e058b3cf Heat a large, non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.
5f7d6051-313a-42b5-a1d1-9a67e058b3cf Add ground turkey, chili powder, garlic powder and cumin to skillet. Cook and stir to crumble until meat is cooked to 165° F, about 6 minutes.
5f7d6051-313a-42b5-a1d1-9a67e058b3cf Season to taste with salt and pepper.
5f7d6051-313a-42b5-a1d1-9a67e058b3cf Divide warm rice into four bowls. Top with turkey, black beans, corn and pico de gallo.
5f7d6051-313a-42b5-a1d1-9a67e058b3cf Drizzle with yogurt sauce. Garnish with cilantro, if desired.
c511de63-9635-49ff-af28-19eb9c236a2d Heat a sauté pan, griddle or grill over medium-high heat.
c511de63-9635-49ff-af28-19eb9c236a2d Add turkey patties and cook 4 minutes on each side.
c511de63-9635-49ff-af28-19eb9c236a2d Add a slice of cheese on each turkey patty and cook until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F (approximately 2 additional minutes).
c511de63-9635-49ff-af28-19eb9c236a2d While turkey patties are cooking, heat buns in the oven or in a toaster (optional).
c511de63-9635-49ff-af28-19eb9c236a2d Spread top and bottom bun with 1 tablespoon each of roasted garlic mayo. Add bibb lettuce and 1/4 cup of the cherry pepper relish to both buns.
c511de63-9635-49ff-af28-19eb9c236a2d Place turkey patty on top of the relish, then add the top bun.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 Prior to cooking turkey patties, prepare the red onion cranberry relish and Southwest slaw. These elements can be made 1-2 days prior to serving burgers.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 For the relish, heat a sauté pan over medium-high heat. Add onions and cook until soft and beginning to brown. Add canned whole berry cranberry sauce to the pan and cook for 5 minutes. Reduce to a simmer until the liquid is cooked out. Set aside.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 To prepare the Southwest slaw, mix together all of the ingredients. Allow to sit for a minimum of 1 hour.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 For the turkey patties, heat a sauté pan, griddle or grill over medium-high heat. Once the cooking surface is hot, add the turkey patties and cook 4 minutes on each side.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 Top each turkey patty with a slice of cheese and continue to cook until burgers reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F, approximately 2 additional minutes.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 While turkey patties are cooking, heat the buns in the oven or in a toaster (optional).
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 Spread each bottom bun with 1 tablespoon of chipotle mayo. Then add 1/4 cup of the red onion cranberry relish.
e8f557d9-b343-4fad-8003-99bfd9e13e14 Place turkey patty on top of the relish, then top with Southwest slaw. Top with bun.
931ebd1c-c6af-46da-bdcc-ea16d738aada Heat a large sauté pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Add vegetable oil.
931ebd1c-c6af-46da-bdcc-ea16d738aada Once oil is hot, add Fajita seasoning and turkey breast cutlets. Cook for 5 minutes, then add onions and peppers to the pan. Cook until the fajita strips reach a minimum internal temperature of 165 °F, and onions and peppers are soft and slightly browned, approximately 5 additional minutes.
931ebd1c-c6af-46da-bdcc-ea16d738aada Add the Turkey Fajita strips and onions/peppers on a platter.
