931ebd1c-c6af-46da-bdcc-ea16d738aada Microwave flour tortillas until warm.
931ebd1c-c6af-46da-bdcc-ea16d738aada Place pico, guacamole, shredded cheese and favorite salsa into separate bowls as toppings.
931ebd1c-c6af-46da-bdcc-ea16d738aada Layer warm tortillas with turkey strips and top with your favorite toppings.
90bd5733-7474-4a45-b6dc-001ecf7f649f Combine broth and apple cider in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Once boiling, lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until reduced by about half.
90bd5733-7474-4a45-b6dc-001ecf7f649f Add soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and poultry seasoning to the mixture.
90bd5733-7474-4a45-b6dc-001ecf7f649f In a separate saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
90bd5733-7474-4a45-b6dc-001ecf7f649f Add flour to the butter and whisk until pale golden brown, about 2 minutes.
90bd5733-7474-4a45-b6dc-001ecf7f649f Turn off the heat and let butter mixture cool for one minute. Add broth mixture, whisking vigorously until smooth.
90bd5733-7474-4a45-b6dc-001ecf7f649f Raise heat to medium and bring gravy to a boil, then season to taste with salt and pepper.
d9f9d700-c9fa-41a5-85a8-495717f61bf1 Peel sweet potatoes and onion and dice into 1/2 inch pieces.
d9f9d700-c9fa-41a5-85a8-495717f61bf1 Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add olive oil.
d9f9d700-c9fa-41a5-85a8-495717f61bf1 Add sweet potatoes and onions to the skillet with oil and season with a pinch of salt.
d9f9d700-c9fa-41a5-85a8-495717f61bf1 Cook, stirring from time to time for 5 minutes, until onions begin to turn golden brown and potatoes soften.
d9f9d700-c9fa-41a5-85a8-495717f61bf1 Add turkey breast strips and season with another pinch of salt, ground pepper and dried thyme. Continue to cook, stirring until the turkey is cooked to 165°F and brown on the edges, about 4-5 minutes.
d9f9d700-c9fa-41a5-85a8-495717f61bf1 Garnish with parsley and top with poached eggs.
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 For the turkey burgers heat a sauté pan or griddle over medium high heat. Once pan or griddle is hot, place the turkey burgers on the skillet or griddle and cook 4 minutes then flip.
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 Cook for 2 minutes then place a slice of cheese on each turkey burger and cook until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F (approximately 2 additional minutes). Use a meat thermometer to confirm internal temperature.
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 While turkey burgers are cooking, heat the buns in the oven or in a toaster (Optional).
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 Once cooked, place buns on clean/sanitized work surface. Spread bottom bun with 2 Tbsp. each of ranch.
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 Next top with bibb lettuce, then a slice of tomato.
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 Place turkey burger on top of the tomato. Then place two slices of peppered bacon on top of turkey burger and two slices of avocado. Place top bun over the Turkey burger.
170388e1-ed72-43af-87f4-befaae0ad164 Place on a platter and serve immediately.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 Prior to cooking the turkey burgers prepare the pickled red onions and the shredded cabbage mix.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 For the shredded cabbage mix, mix together all of the ingredients. Allow to sit for a minimum of 1 hour.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 For the turkey burgers heat a sauté pan or griddle over medium high heat. Once pan or griddle is hot, place the turkey burgers on the skillet or griddle and cook 4 minutes then flip.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 Cook for 2 minutes then place a slice of cheese on each turkey burger and cook until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F (approximately 2 additional minutes). Use a meat thermometer to confirm internal temperature.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 While turkey burgers are cooking, heat the buns in the oven or in a toaster (optional).
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 Once cooked, place buns on clean/sanitized work surface. Spread bottom bun with 1 tablespoon. each of avocado ranch.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 Next top ¼ cup shredded cabbage mix, then ¼ cup pickled red onions.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 Place turkey burger on top of the onions, then place the guacamole on top of turkey burger, place top bun over the turkey burger.
adcf9352-29a8-49f8-86bf-ac6d83d2d5e9 Place on a platter and serve immediately.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Heat a sauté pan or griddle over medium high heat.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Once pan or griddle is hot, place the turkey burgers on the skillet or griddle and cook 4 minutes then flip.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Cook until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F (approximately 4 additional minutes). Use a meat thermometer to confirm internal temperature.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 While turkey burgers are cooking, heat the buns in the oven or in a toaster (Optional).
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Once cooked, place buns on clean/sanitized work surface. Spread top and bottom bun with 1 Tbsp. each of Tzatziki sauce or Dill Dip.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Next, top with the baby spinach and the cucumber relish.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Place Turkey Burger on top of the relish, then place the top bun over the Turkey burger.
dd0dab4b-04d3-4b7d-888e-0acf76b62780 Place on a platter and serve immediately.
3a782328-5d33-445b-9174-630820cf54df Mix the turkey with the rest of the marinade ingredients. Allow to marinade for at least 2 hours or overnight.
3a782328-5d33-445b-9174-630820cf54df Meanwhile, mix the glaze ingredients in a small sauce pan. Bring to a simmer and whisk to combine. Simmer about 10 minutes and remove from heat.
3a782328-5d33-445b-9174-630820cf54df Build the skewers by placing one square of red pepper onto the skewer, followed by 2 squares of turkey, pressing the skewer into the center of the turkey squares and pushing them right up close to the pepper like the pages of a book. Repeat 3 times, and bookend with a 5th pepper.
3a782328-5d33-445b-9174-630820cf54df Grill the turkey on high heat on all four sides, about 4 minutes per side, until browned and cooked through.
3a782328-5d33-445b-9174-630820cf54df Line the skewers on a platter and drizzle with the glaze. Sprinkle on the sesame seeds and chopped basil before serving.
d5f0cf34-c5ff-40b1-9f86-35dd3ba973d4 In a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil. After oil is hot, add butter.
d5f0cf34-c5ff-40b1-9f86-35dd3ba973d4 Add about 6 lemon slices to the skillet.
d5f0cf34-c5ff-40b1-9f86-35dd3ba973d4 Sprinkle the turkey breast cutlets with garlic powder, salt and pepper, and cayenne pepper (if desired).
d5f0cf34-c5ff-40b1-9f86-35dd3ba973d4 Place the turkey breast cutlets into the skillet and cook for about 3 minutes on each side until the turkey is no longer pink, and is slightly browned around the edges.
d5f0cf34-c5ff-40b1-9f86-35dd3ba973d4 Turkey is fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
d5f0cf34-c5ff-40b1-9f86-35dd3ba973d4 Garnish with sprigs of fresh thyme.
b604e4b6-d8e7-4c4a-9756-4a0de76aa597 In a medium bowl, gently mix the ground turkey with the spinach, feta, oregano, garlic, onion, salt, and pepper. Roll into 1-inch rounds and set aside.
b604e4b6-d8e7-4c4a-9756-4a0de76aa597 Place a skillet over medium heat and add a teaspoon or so of olive oil.
b604e4b6-d8e7-4c4a-9756-4a0de76aa597 Cook the meatballs in batches, making sure to brown on all sides.
b604e4b6-d8e7-4c4a-9756-4a0de76aa597 Once all the meatballs are cooked through, divide between your plates and add your favorites - pitas, hummus, tzatziki, olives, salad, tomatoes.
07379083-aea4-462b-98fd-b4be2ff0a89f Heat a saucepan with the avocado oil over medium high heat. Cut the turkey breast into small pieces and sauté until cooked through. Midway through cooking, add the chopped onion. When the turkey is cooked, add the taco seasoning.
07379083-aea4-462b-98fd-b4be2ff0a89f Add the black beans, salsa, corn, green chilies, enchilada sauce, and rice. Stir well.
07379083-aea4-462b-98fd-b4be2ff0a89f Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring every few minutes, until the rice is cooked through. Be careful not to let the bottom scorch. If the casserole begins sticking, reduce the heat further.
07379083-aea4-462b-98fd-b4be2ff0a89f When the rice is cooked through, remove from the heat and let sit for about 5 minutes.
07379083-aea4-462b-98fd-b4be2ff0a89f Serve over tortilla shells and top with desired toppings.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Place mushrooms into a small food processor and grind.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Place mushrooms and onions in a large microwave safe bowl.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Microwave on high for 2 minutes. Drain any liquid out. Let cool.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Add ground turkey, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to bowl. Mix until just combined.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Form into 4 patties. Refrigerate for 30 minutes, or overnight.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Preheat grill to high heat. Oil grates well.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Cook until cooked through, about 3 to 4 minutes per side. During last minute of grilling, add cheese.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Let rest for 5 minutes.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Place burgers on buns.
05fd2826-333f-48b1-958d-1e758990bc62 Top with a little over a tablespoon of dressing, 1 bacon slice and 2 slices avocado.
8e32a97b-6509-43c4-b98f-eb791c872f98 In a large skillet, brown the ground turkey over medium heat. Transfer the ground turkey, remaining ingredients plus ½ cup water to your slow cooker.
8e32a97b-6509-43c4-b98f-eb791c872f98 Stir and cook on low for 3-4 hours.
8e32a97b-6509-43c4-b98f-eb791c872f98 Serve your sloppy joes over lettuce or your favorite buns.
70888cf3-1264-4410-96c3-6da83b2c20db Heat a sauté pan or griddle over medium high heat. Place 2 tbsp. of olive oil in pan, then add single slices of prosciutto and cook until crispy. Remove and place on a paper towel to drain.
70888cf3-1264-4410-96c3-6da83b2c20db Using the same pan, add the turkey tenderloin pieces in the pan and sauté until lightly browned and heated throughout (approximately 4 minutes). Note: turkey tenderloin pieces can be served cold over the salad if desired.
70888cf3-1264-4410-96c3-6da83b2c20db While the turkey bites are heating, place the chopped kale, red grapes, pistachios and apples in a mixing bowl. Add the dressing and gently toss until thoroughly coated.
70888cf3-1264-4410-96c3-6da83b2c20db Place mixed salad on a large platter, then top with turkey bites and crispy prosciutto. Break up the parmesan crisps and sprinkle over the entire salad.
70888cf3-1264-4410-96c3-6da83b2c20db Serve immediately.
70888cf3-1264-4410-96c3-6da83b2c20db Note: to prevent apples from browning, squeeze 1 lemon into a container and add 2 cups of water. Slice the apples and place in the liquid until needed.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Preheat your oven to 375°F degrees.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Begin by rinsing your quinoa thoroughly.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d In a greased 9x13 pan, add the rinsed quinoa to the bottom of the pan.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d In a sauce pan, heat the spaghetti sauce and chicken broth until hot. Remove from the stovetop and pour the liquid over the quinoa, until it is fully covered.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Place meatballs on top of the quinoa and finish with thin slices of mozzarella (you can put them over the meatball or just dabble on top of the dish).
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Cover the dish tightly with foil and bake for 35-40 minutes. During the last 5-10 minutes, remove the foil to melt the cheese fully.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d While the dish is baking, pour balsamic vinegar into a small saucepan. Turn heat to medium high and bring vinegar to a boil.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Once boiling, reduce to simmer and let simmer for about 10 minutes until vinegar has reduced down. Stir occasionally. When it begins to coat the back of a spoon, you will know that it is fully reduced. Set aside to cool while the casserole bakes.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Cook until the meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
9fd4683b-c5bb-45a2-abe4-fa14bb2a630d Once your dish is done baking, garnish with thinly sliced basil and your balsamic reduction.
01431123-eebe-4567-97b8-ed33fdd5556e Take the turkey breast strips out of the package and rinse under cold water. Pat dry lightly with paper towel and place in a bowl. Toss with olive oil and season with salt and pepper, to taste.
01431123-eebe-4567-97b8-ed33fdd5556e Thread turkey strips onto skewers and place on a platter.
01431123-eebe-4567-97b8-ed33fdd5556e Grill the turkey for 2 minutes per side or until fully cooked through. Turkey is fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
01431123-eebe-4567-97b8-ed33fdd5556e Add the remaining salad ingredients into a large bowl and toss with the dressing. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve immediately.
912755f2-ca05-432a-ab35-4238eaa06972 Prepare the sliders. Divide the turkey into 8 equal balls. Shape each ball into a patty approximately 3" across, or about the size of the slider buns. Cover and refrigerate until needed.
912755f2-ca05-432a-ab35-4238eaa06972 Season the sliders with salt and pepper, as desired. On a grill or in a sauté pan, cook over medium heat for 5-8 minutes or until an internal temperature of 165°F is reached on a meat thermometer.
912755f2-ca05-432a-ab35-4238eaa06972 Spread the mayo evenly on the buns.
912755f2-ca05-432a-ab35-4238eaa06972 When the sliders are cooked, remove from heat and place on the bottom buns.
912755f2-ca05-432a-ab35-4238eaa06972 Place 2 slices of tomato on each sandwich. Add the bacon and lettuce. Close the sandwiches, and serve!
d1222ed6-caa7-4f63-b6cf-1b174e01513b To prep the Citrus Turkey Cutlets, combine all ingredients except turkey in a food processor. Blend to a coarse puree.
d1222ed6-caa7-4f63-b6cf-1b174e01513b Place turkey in a gallon freezer bag. Add marinade.
d1222ed6-caa7-4f63-b6cf-1b174e01513b Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
d1222ed6-caa7-4f63-b6cf-1b174e01513b To cook the Citrus Turkey Cutlets and prepare a Cilantro Chimichurri, make the chimichurri. Combine the cilantro, parsley, garlic, red pepper flakes, cumin, salt, and red wine vinegar in the bowl of a food processor. Puree until smooth. Adjust seasoning with salt and red pepper as needed.
d1222ed6-caa7-4f63-b6cf-1b174e01513b Stir in olive oil. Serve at room temperature.
d1222ed6-caa7-4f63-b6cf-1b174e01513b Remove the turkey cutlets from the marinade and grill over medium heat for about 4 minutes per side, or until an internal temperature of 165°F is reached on a meat thermometer.
223dfaa4-fe41-4551-b6ee-b11eb33acdca To prep the Citrus Turkey Cutlets, combine all ingredients except turkey in a food processor. Blend to a coarse puree.
223dfaa4-fe41-4551-b6ee-b11eb33acdca Place turkey in a gallon freezer bag. Add marinade.
223dfaa4-fe41-4551-b6ee-b11eb33acdca Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
223dfaa4-fe41-4551-b6ee-b11eb33acdca To prepare the salad, make the vinaigrette. Combine the red wine vinegar, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper. Stir until salt is dissolved. Slowly whisk in the olive oil. Reserve.
223dfaa4-fe41-4551-b6ee-b11eb33acdca Remove the turkey cutlets from the marinade and grill over medium heat for about 4 minutes per side, or until an internal temperature of 165¬F is reached on a meat thermometer.
223dfaa4-fe41-4551-b6ee-b11eb33acdca Toss the salad ingredients, including field greens, avocado, grape tomatoes, and red onion, with enough vinaigrette to lightly coat. Pile the salad in the center of plate.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f TIP: Skip to step 9 if using Honeysuckle White HomeStyle Turkey Meatloaf
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray a 9x5" loaf pan with food release spray and then line with aluminum foil.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Heat oil in a sauté pan until shimmering. Add the onions and sauté over medium heat for 4-5 minutes, or until softened.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Add the garlic and sauté for 1 minute. Add the mushrooms, salt, and pepper. Increase heat to high and sauté mushrooms, stirring frequently for about 5 minutes or until done.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Transfer the onions and mushrooms to a large bowl. Stir in soy sauce and ketchup.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Combine the panko breadcrumbs and milk in a small bowl. Add the eggs and stir well to combine.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Add the breadcrumb-egg mixture to the sautéed mushrooms, and then add the ground turkey.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Using a rubber spatula or your hand, gently mix all ingredients until combined. Do not over mix.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Scrape the meatloaf mixture into the foil-lined pan and smooth the top.
b6101c56-ec0b-431d-9253-b1df5198c07f Bake for 50-55 minutes or until a meat thermometer reads 165°F.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray a 9x5" loaf pan with food release spray and then line with aluminum foil.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c To create the glaze, combine ketchup, brown sugar, white vinegar, and red pepper flakes in a small bowl. Stir until blended and set aside.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Heat oil in a sauté pan until shimmering. Add the onions and sauté over medium heat for 4-5 minutes, or until softened.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Add the garlic and sauté for 1 minute.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Add the mushrooms, salt, and pepper. Increase heat to high and sauté mushrooms, stirring frequently for about 5 minutes or until done.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Transfer the onions and mushrooms to a large bowl. Stir in soy sauce and ketchup.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Combine the panko breadcrumbs and milk in a small bowl. Add the eggs and stir well to combine.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Add the breadcrumb-egg mixture to the sautéed mushrooms, and then add the ground turkey.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Using a rubber spatula or your hand, gently mix all ingredients until combined. Do not over mix.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Scrape the meatloaf mixture into the foil-lined pan and smooth the top.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Brush about 1/2 cup of glaze evenly over the meatloaf. Cover with a layer of aluminum foil.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Bake for 40 minutes, then remove foil.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Continue baking 5-10 more minutes, or until a meat thermometer reads 165°F.
11420850-1527-4cdc-b09e-a293aa74cd7c Let rest 5 minutes before slicing, and serve with remaining glaze.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Preheat the oven to 350°F.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Stir breadcrumbs and milk together in a large bowl and let sit for 5 minutes. Add the egg, cheese, parsley, oregano, and salt. Stir until well blended.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Add the ground turkey and use a fork, or your fingers, to gently mix until combined. Do not over mix.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Divide the mixture into 12 equal portions.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Wet your hands. Form each turkey portion into a ball around a cube of mozzarella.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Place the meatballs on a half sheet pan and bake for 10-15 minutes or until a meat thermometer reaches 165°F.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 While meatballs are baking, prepare the tomato sauce.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Heat the olive oil in a sauté pan over medium high heat until shimmering. Add the diced onion and dried basil, and sauté for 2 minutes.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Add the minced garlic and sauté for one minute.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Add the crushed tomatoes and simmer for 10-15 minutes.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 After removing the meatballs from the oven, transfer to simmering tomato sauce. Stir gently to coat.
12c35a55-00b3-4407-ba08-4ec7f1b115b5 Sprinkle with Italian parsley and parmesan cheese, and enjoy!
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe To prepare the cheese-stuffed meatballs, preheat the oven to 350°F.
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe Stir breadcrumbs and milk together in a large bowl and let sit for 5 minutes. Add the egg, cheese, parsley, oregano, and salt. Stir until well blended.
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe Add the ground turkey and use a fork, or your fingers, to gently mix until combined. Do not over mix.
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe Divide the mixture into 12 equal portions. Wet your hands. Form each turkey portion into a ball around a cube of mozzarella.
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe Place the meatballs on a half sheet pan and bake for 10-15 minutes or until a meat thermometer reaches 165°F.
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe While the meatballs are cooking, spread mayonnaise evenly on hoagie buns, then add giardiniera relish (available at most grocery stores, near the pickles/olives).
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe Once the meatballs are finished baking, place 3 on each bun.
4061eed6-5a50-4106-87ae-bf382f2fdcfe Top with thinly sliced red onion rings and sliced tomatoes.
0c5af798-e693-4439-a7c9-dc6a6f474e87 Cook turkey tenderloins per package instructions. Place in refrigerator to cool. Once turkey is cool, shred or dice into 1/2 inch cubes. (Your preference)
0c5af798-e693-4439-a7c9-dc6a6f474e87 Combine turkey, cashews, celery, sour cream, cream cheese, cranberries, and onions in a bowl and mix. Salt and pepper to taste.
0c5af798-e693-4439-a7c9-dc6a6f474e87 To serve, split croissant. Assemble lettuce and tomato on the bottom bun. Top with 3-4 tablespoons of turkey and place top bun.
007e5ec5-ec8b-4dd5-9bd6-75e5bce72171 For the turkey burgers, heat a saute pan or griddle over medium high heat. Once pan or griddle is hot, place the turkey burgers on the skillet or griddle and cook 4 minutes then flip. Continue to cook, approximately 4 additional minutes, until they reach a minimum internal temperature of 165°F.
007e5ec5-ec8b-4dd5-9bd6-75e5bce72171 While turkey burger is cooking, spread garlic mayonnaise on bottom bun.
007e5ec5-ec8b-4dd5-9bd6-75e5bce72171 Once burgers are cooked, remove from grill/griddle. Begin assembly by placing turkey patty on top of the bottom bun. Top turkey patty with arugula, cranberry sauce, red onion and feta cheese. Place top bun and serve.
e288c52e-41fb-40c1-9207-02519392e8c2 Cook pasta according to instructions on box. Set aside until ready to serve. (Do not add to soup while cooking as it will absorb the stock and expand.)
e288c52e-41fb-40c1-9207-02519392e8c2 Place olive oil in large stock pot. Cook turkey and sausage until brown and internal temperature is 165°F. Do not drain any of the fat. Remove the turkey and sausage and set aside.
e288c52e-41fb-40c1-9207-02519392e8c2 In the same stock pot, add the garlic, onions, carrots and celery. Cook until softened. Add the turkey and sausage back into the pot and stir.
e288c52e-41fb-40c1-9207-02519392e8c2 Add the chicken stock, tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, basil, oregano, thyme and salt and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes.
e288c52e-41fb-40c1-9207-02519392e8c2 After 30 minutes, add the beans and cook an additional 10 minutes.
e288c52e-41fb-40c1-9207-02519392e8c2 Prior to serving, add the pasta. Garnish with freshly grated parmesan.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Heat a cast iron skillet or griddle over medium high heat and when hot, grease lightly with a teaspoon of oil.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Transfer the turkey burgers to the skillet or griddle and cook 4 minutes then flip.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Cook another 2 minutes then place a slice of cheese on each burger and cook for another 2 minutes. Use a meat thermometer to confirm internal temperature is 165°F throughout each burger.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Meanwhile, heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add the remaining oil, then the mushrooms.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Sprinkle mushrooms with a pinch of salt and cook until they begin to brown, about 5 minutes.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Combine mustard and mayonnaise in a small bowl and mix. Spread mustard and mayonnaise mixture on the inside of each toasted bun.
a143e867-2fe3-4f62-ac94-772d5fe211c3 Place the cooked burgers on the bottom bun. Add a spoonful of the mushrooms on top of the cheese. Top with top buns and serve.
dfadbfb1-a822-4568-a33d-936e50f41108 Cut the wings into three pieces at the joints, reserving the wing tips for another use if desired.
dfadbfb1-a822-4568-a33d-936e50f41108 Combine the soy sauce, maple syrup, apple cider vinegar, garlic and ginger in a bowl and reserve 1/3 cup. Transfer the 1/3 cup to a container and store in the refrigerator.
dfadbfb1-a822-4568-a33d-936e50f41108 Place the two larger sections of the wings into a large zip top plastic bag. Pour the rest of the marinade into the bag. Seal the bag and refrigerate the wings. Allow the wings to marinate for at least 8 hours or overnight.
dfadbfb1-a822-4568-a33d-936e50f41108 Heat the oven to 300 degrees. Line a baking pan with foil, then spray the foil with non-stick spray or oil.
dfadbfb1-a822-4568-a33d-936e50f41108 Place the wings on the pan skin side up, cover with foil and bake for 2 hours then uncover, flip the wings, cover again with foil and bake for another 30 minutes, or until the turkey wings are fork tender and a meat thermometer registers 165°F.
dfadbfb1-a822-4568-a33d-936e50f41108 Remove the foil, flip the wings again and place a few inches under the broiler. Broil for 5-10 minutes, basting frequently with the reserved marinade, until the skin is brown and sticky.
0cf3dd73-73fb-4e5e-b19b-455587a4ba1b Heat a large heavy skillet over medium high heat and add the oil.
0cf3dd73-73fb-4e5e-b19b-455587a4ba1b Place drumsticks in the skillet and brown on all sides.
0cf3dd73-73fb-4e5e-b19b-455587a4ba1b Place the potatoes, carrots, onions and garlic in an oval 5-6 quart slow cooker. Place drumsticks on top of the vegetables.
0cf3dd73-73fb-4e5e-b19b-455587a4ba1b Combine the broth, Worcestershire sauce and salt in a small bowl and pour over the drumsticks. Sprinkle the drumsticks with the poultry seasoning.
0cf3dd73-73fb-4e5e-b19b-455587a4ba1b Cover and cook on LOW until the turkey and vegetables are tender, about 6 hours.
0cf3dd73-73fb-4e5e-b19b-455587a4ba1b Serve the turkey with the vegetables. Spoon some of the onions and sauce over the meat and garnish with parsley if desired. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Preheat oven to 325°F. Cooking time will vary by size of bird.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Remove the turkey from the bag. Remove giblet package underneath the neck skin area as well as the neck from the body cavity.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Place turkey, breast side up, in a shallow roasting pan. Pat the outside and inside of the turkey dry with paper towels.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Combine salt and black pepper in a small bowl. Season the inside of the turkey with about 1/3 of the salt mixture. Fold wing tips under the bird.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Place the apple, orange and lemon slices, onion, and 2 sprigs of each sage in the main turkey cavity (for aromatics and garnish only). Tie the legs together to hold the shape of the turkey.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat until the edges begin to turn golden, about 2 minutes. Brush outside of the turkey completely with the melted butter. Season with remaining 2/3 of the salt mixture and place in oven for the recommended roasting time.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 If the turkey becomes golden brown before it is fully cooked, cover with a loose tent of aluminum foil to prevent over browning. Cut a hole in the foil to view the pop-up timer.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 For an optimal eating experience, turkey is done when the pop-up timer has popped and a meat thermometer registers at 170°F, in the deepest part of the breast and thickest part of the inner-thigh.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 To prepare the Caramelized Apples & Oranges, heat oven to 375°F.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 In a large bowl, toss together the apples, oranges, orange juice, cinnamon, salt, and brown sugar. Mound the apple mixture in baking pan or casserole and scatter the butter over the top.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Bake for 30 minutes, then take out and toss with a large spoon to coat and place back in the oven for another 30 minutes.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 After taking it out of the oven, carefully stir and let dish rest roughly 10 minutes before serving.
22faba24-101c-485d-8d9b-bc376a64d1e1 Remove the turkey from the oven and allow to rest for 20-30 minutes before slicing. Garnish serving dish with caramelized apples & oranges, sage sprigs and fig slices.
d17ef828-0ab0-4b74-a400-d4fac61b5b3a Remove the turkey from the fridge one hour before roasting. Remove the giblets and neck. Rinse the turkey, pat dry and allow to come to room temperature.
d17ef828-0ab0-4b74-a400-d4fac61b5b3a To make the chimichurri butter, place the parsley, scallions, garlic, and oregano in the food processor. Pulse until finely chopped, stopping to scrape down the sides of the bowl as necessary. Add the butter and the vinegar, mix well to combine, making sure the butter is smooth and the herbs evenly mixed throughout, place in a bowl and add the red pepper flakes and olive oil. Mix well and set aside. Rub the chimichurri butter all over the turkey.
d17ef828-0ab0-4b74-a400-d4fac61b5b3a Preheat the oven to 450°F. Position a rack in the lower third of the oven. Place the turkey in a large roasting pan. Pour 3 cups of chicken broth into the bottom of the roasting pan. Place the turkey in the oven and turn down the heat to 350°F. Cook for about 3 hours (until the turkey registers 170°F on a meat thermometer), baste the turkey with the drippings about 4 times throughout cooking.
d17ef828-0ab0-4b74-a400-d4fac61b5b3a Remove the turkey from the oven, transfer the turkey to a baking sheet or platter, tent loosely with foil and let rest for about 30 minutes before slicing.
0456a6dd-5d23-4c18-b470-1e16528c37f7 In a large skillet, heat a teaspoon of the oil over medium heat. Add the ground turkey and cook, stirring often, until no pink remains. Remove the turkey to a plate.
0456a6dd-5d23-4c18-b470-1e16528c37f7 Heat the remaining oil in the skillet and add the onion, bell pepper, and squash. Sauté until the onions start to soften - 3-4 minutes. Stir in the garlic, ginger, and spices and sauté until fragrant, another minute or two.
0456a6dd-5d23-4c18-b470-1e16528c37f7 Add the turkey back to the pan along with the tomatoes and coconut milk. Season with salt and pepper. Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to a steady simmer, cover, and continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until the butternut squash is softened.
0456a6dd-5d23-4c18-b470-1e16528c37f7 Serve the mixture with a swirl of Greek yogurt, a sprinkling of fresh chopped cilantro, and rice, if desired.
0456a6dd-5d23-4c18-b470-1e16528c37f7 Recipe and images courtesy of 'Neighborfood'
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Apple Cider Brine: In a large stock pot over medium-high heat, add the ingredients listed under the Apple Cider Brine heading. Bring the brine to a boil. Then remove the brine from the hot stove and let it cool to room temperature.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Place the thawed, unwrapped turkey in a brining bag or in a large container, and pour the cooled Apple Cider Brine over the turkey.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Seal the bag and refrigerate it for 12 to 24 hours. The larger the turkey, the longer it should remain in the brine.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d After the allotted time, remove the turkey from the brine and rinse inside and out.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Roast Turkey: Preheat the oven to 325°F.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Rub the turkey with softened butter on the outside of the skin all over and under the skin as well.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Sprinkle the buttered turkey all over with salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Wrap the wing tips and the ends of the turkey legs with foil to prevent them from overcooking.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Place turkey on a rack inside a roasting pan.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Pour chicken broth into the bottom of the roasting pan.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Place a foil tent over the turkey and leave it on for the first hour of cooking.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Place the turkey in a preheated oven. Cook the turkey for about 15 minutes per pound. For a 12-pound turkey, cook for about 3 hours or until a meat thermometer reads 170°F.
0d51ee56-6f6b-4b7d-8112-75390883944d Remove the turkey from the oven and let it rest for about 30 minutes.
3abfe08c-941f-49b1-b108-499ada2edd14 In medium bowl, combine mango salsa ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
3abfe08c-941f-49b1-b108-499ada2edd14 Grill tenderloins approximately 20 to 30 minutes, turning every 5 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165° F.
3abfe08c-941f-49b1-b108-499ada2edd14 To serve, slice tenderloins and top with mango salsa.
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c Preheat oven to 350°F
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c Cook Turkey Breast Tenderloins per package instructions.
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in skillet. sauté onion, pepper and garlic over medium heat until tender, about 3 minutes.
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c Squeeze any excess moisture from spinach. Along with the turkey, add to skillet. sauté 1 minute. Remove from heat.
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, and salt. Beat well.
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c Add the sautéed contents of skillet and Swiss cheese to bowl. Mix well.
03d89c80-aed2-4137-aaec-f323b8f9b76c Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for approximately 65 minutes or until center is set.
d81f857b-f469-4594-9e6c-1836be6f0d10 Prepare turkey breast tenderloins per package instructions. Let turkey cool. Once cooled, shred or cut into 1" 1/2" cubes.
d81f857b-f469-4594-9e6c-1836be6f0d10 In large bowl, combine Napa cabbage, red cabbage, red peppers, red onions, and shredded carrots. Gently toss.
d81f857b-f469-4594-9e6c-1836be6f0d10 Add turkey and 1 cup dressing to the bowl and mix.
d81f857b-f469-4594-9e6c-1836be6f0d10 Garnish with fried wonton strips, green onions, and sesame seeds.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa Preheat oven to 350°F.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa Cook pasta and turkey sausage according to package instructions. (Slice turkey sausage links into 1/4 inch pieces before cooking).
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa In a medium saucepan, combine turkey sausage and pasta sauce. Heat thoroughly. Set aside 1 cup for preparation.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa While sauce and turkey are cooking, combine Ricotta cheese, 1 cup mozzarella, egg, dried basil, salt and garlic salt in a bowl. Mix well.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa Gently fold in the cooked pasta to the cheese mixture.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa Spread the reserved 1 cup of sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Spread pasta mixture over the top of the sauce.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup mozzarella and parmesan cheese.
a8da3bd3-98b8-44ce-bba3-b8234b223aaa Bake uncovered for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.
46ce33a9-0390-4316-a4c8-e11cec9376be Preheat oven to 375°F. Heat a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook until evenly browned.
46ce33a9-0390-4316-a4c8-e11cec9376be Prepare stuffing according to package instructions (using chicken broth and melted butter).
46ce33a9-0390-4316-a4c8-e11cec9376be Add cooked sausage and drippings to the stuffing. Mix well.
46ce33a9-0390-4316-a4c8-e11cec9376be Place mixture into a buttered casserole dish. Bake until golden brown and crisp.
94879642-3c6a-433b-8ff2-b2c71dcf6c42 Heat a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook until evenly browned.
94879642-3c6a-433b-8ff2-b2c71dcf6c42 Pour turkey juices into a saucepan.
94879642-3c6a-433b-8ff2-b2c71dcf6c42 In a small bowl, combine cornstarch with 2 tablespoons chicken broth; mix until there are no lumps.
94879642-3c6a-433b-8ff2-b2c71dcf6c42 Pour remaining chicken broth into the saucepan. Heat chicken broth and turkey juices to a simmer. Add cornstarch mixture to the saucepan, and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
94879642-3c6a-433b-8ff2-b2c71dcf6c42 Add browned sausage to the gravy.
94879642-3c6a-433b-8ff2-b2c71dcf6c42 Add salt and pepper to taste.
0af26a02-4a33-4db2-b8cc-77ca004049b8 Heat a nonstick pan over medium heat and add the oil.
0af26a02-4a33-4db2-b8cc-77ca004049b8 Place turkey breast cutlets on a plate and coat with flour.
0af26a02-4a33-4db2-b8cc-77ca004049b8 Add cutlets to the pan and cook on both sides until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.
0af26a02-4a33-4db2-b8cc-77ca004049b8 Add the orange marmalade, wine and grapes, and stir. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
0af26a02-4a33-4db2-b8cc-77ca004049b8 Remove the turkey to a serving platter.
0af26a02-4a33-4db2-b8cc-77ca004049b8 Add the half and half and salt to pan. Simmer and reduce the sauce until just a few tablespoons remain. Spoon the sauce and grapes over the turkey.
d73e38a0-8417-4344-be71-2a2dc6363830 In saucepan, combine apple cider vinegar, Truvia sweetener, and mustard; bring to boil over medium-high heat. Cook for 10-12 minutes or until reduced by half.
d73e38a0-8417-4344-be71-2a2dc6363830 Meanwhile, preheat oven to 450°F. Pat turkey breast dry with paper towel. Stir together butter, thyme, garlic, salt and pepper; rub all over turkey, including under the skin.
d73e38a0-8417-4344-be71-2a2dc6363830 Place turkey on rack in roasting pan; roast for 40 minutes. Reduce heat to 400°F; roast, basting with apple cider glaze for about 30 minutes or until thermometer inserted into thickest part of the breast reaches 165°F. If turkey browns too quickly, cover loosely with foil. Slice turkey and serve. Delicious with cranberry sauce! Substitute rosemary or marjoram for thyme, if desired.
a4a83a11-d22e-41eb-8c8f-f781794afd47 Stir together paprika, chili powder, salt, onion powder, garlic powder, mustard powder, cumin, oregano, Truvia blend and pepper.
a4a83a11-d22e-41eb-8c8f-f781794afd47 Preheat oven to 400°F. Remove neck and giblets from turkey; reserve turkey for roasting pan. Pat turkey dry with paper towel. Rub turkey all over, including under skin and inside cavity, with butter and seasoning mixture.
a4a83a11-d22e-41eb-8c8f-f781794afd47 Place on rack in roasting pan. Add neck, giblets, onion, celery and garlic to pan; roast for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°F; roast for 2.5 hours or until thermometer inserted into thickest part of the breast registers 170°F. If turkey browns too quickly, cover loosely with foil.
a4a83a11-d22e-41eb-8c8f-f781794afd47 Carefully transfer turkey to cutting board and tent loosely with foil. Let stand 30 minutes before carving.
a4a83a11-d22e-41eb-8c8f-f781794afd47 Meanwhile, skim off fat in roasting pan; stir in broth and barbecue sauce. Use your favorite flavored barbecue sauces, such as spicy or sweet.
a4a83a11-d22e-41eb-8c8f-f781794afd47 Cook over medium heat, stirring to scrape up brown bits from bottom of pan; bring to boil. Whisk cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of water; stir into pan. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer for 6-8 minutes or until thickened and flavorful. Strain and serve with turkey.
71bf6fc4-d842-4d29-b254-3a204e00b069 In food processor, combine parsley, cilantro, basil and garlic; pulse until finely chopped. Add olive oil, lemon zest, lemon juice, salt, pepper, paprika, cumin, coriander, and hot pepper flakes (optional); puree until smooth. Tip: Substitute 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper for hot pepper flakes if desired.
71bf6fc4-d842-4d29-b254-3a204e00b069 Remove neck and giblets from turkey (reserve for another use). Trim excess fat from turkey and discard. Pat turkey dry with paper towel. Rub turkey all over, including under skin and inside cavity, with 3/4 cup herb sauce. Refrigerate turkey for at least 1 hour or up to 4 hours.
71bf6fc4-d842-4d29-b254-3a204e00b069 Preheat grill to high; grease grate well. Turn off burners in center of grill and reduce heat to medium (try to maintain temperature of 350°F). For grills with only two burners, cook on one side of the grill over indirect heat.
71bf6fc4-d842-4d29-b254-3a204e00b069 Place turkey breast side up, on center of grill. Cook, covered, over indirect heat, basting with remaining herb mixture, for 2.5-3 hours or until thermometer inserted into thickest part of the breast reaches 170°F.
71bf6fc4-d842-4d29-b254-3a204e00b069 Carefully transfer turkey to cutting board and tent loosely with foil. Let stand for 30 minutes before carving.
61bd2753-4434-4d9d-b874-fa28132b3b66 Preheat oven to 350°F. Arrange half of the bacon strips side by side on parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Weave remaining strips over and under to create lattice pattern. Freeze for about 15 minutes or until firm.
61bd2753-4434-4d9d-b874-fa28132b3b66 Meanwhile, remove neck and giblets from turkey; reserve for roasting pan. Pat turkey dry with paper towel. Whisk together maple syrup, mustard, thyme, salt and pepper; rub all over turkey, including under skin and inside cavity. Tie legs together with kitchen string and tuck in wing tips. Place turkey breast side up, on rack in roasting pan. Place bacon lattice over top to cover breasts and legs. Arrange onions, celery and carrots around turkey.
61bd2753-4434-4d9d-b874-fa28132b3b66 Cover with foil and roast for 2.5 hours, basting occasionally with drippings. Remove foil; cook for 30-45 minutes or until thermometer inserted into thickest part of breast reads 165°F.
61bd2753-4434-4d9d-b874-fa28132b3b66 Remove kitchen string. Transfer turkey to cutting board and tent loosely with foil. Let rest for 30 minutes before carving.
61bd2753-4434-4d9d-b874-fa28132b3b66 Meanwhile, skim off fat in roasting pan; stir in broth. Cook over medium heat, stirring to scrape up brown bits from bottom of pan; bring to boil. Whisk cornstarch with water; slowly whisk into pan. Simmer for 6-8 minutes or until thickened. Strain and stir in parsley. Serve with turkey and cranberry sauce, if desired.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Start by thawing your turkey in the refrigerator, if frozen, for up to 3 days. If the turkey is larger than 14 lbs., it may take up to 4-5 days.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 To prepare the brine, use a bowl that is larger than the turkey and combine the brine ingredients: water, olive oil, salt, Truvia Brown Sugar Blend, garlic powder, paprika, rosemary, lemon juice and lemon zest. Set aside.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Next, prepare your turkey by remove the giblets and neck from the body cavity and neck cavity of the turkey, and set aside. Trim any fat from the edge of the skin of the turkey, but try to leave as much of the skin on the turkey as you can to protect the meat from drying out during the smoking process.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Rinse the turkey in cold, running water. Make sure to clean the body cavity and outside surfaces of the turkey.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Separate the skin from the breast of the turkey and use your hands to make sure it comes loose. Begin at the back of the bird and move to the front, then down the sides towards the legs which allows the brine to reach the breast meat.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Once this is complete, place the turkey "head first" into the brine mixture. Brine the turkey in the refrigerator for 12 hours or up to 24 hours.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Remove the turkey from the brine and rinse it with cold water, making sure to clean the whole bird, including the outside. Let dry for 5 minutes and pat dry with a paper towel.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 In a small bowl, mix together the dry rub ingredients: paprika, garlic powder, salt, crushed pepper, rosemary, and oregano. Use your hands to distribute the dry rub on the outside of the turkey. TIP: When making the dry rub, you can either use a simple salt/pepper mixture, the dry rub provided in the recipe, or any spice mixture of your choosing.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 When you are ready to smoke your turkey, let your smoker reach a temperature of 225°F. Oil the grate of the smoker to make sure your turkey doesn't stick. TIP: Use a wood smoker for best results. For the wood chips, we suggest hickory chips that have been soaked prior to use.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Maintain a temperature of 225-250°F throughout the entire smoking process. Turkeys take about 40 minutes per pound to smoke, and you want the thickest part of the breast to reach 170°F.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Once the turkey is removed from the smoker, it will continue to cook. Remove the turkey when a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast reaches 170°F, cover with foil, and let rest for 20 minutes.
a81a5d5d-1d16-4ea8-98da-930f27cdca70 Once ready to serve, slice the turkey and serve with lemon slices and fresh rosemary. This smoked turkey recipe makes a great holiday turkey or a weekend meal with plenty of leftovers.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Preheat the oven to 450°F. Spray a wire rack with non-stick spray and place over a large rimmed baking sheet.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 In a small bowl, mix spices together and set aside. Remove giblets and any other parts from inside of the turkey and set aside.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Place turkey on a large, plastic cutting board and pat dry with a paper towel. Make sure your cutting board is dry during this process.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Place turkey breast side down onto the cutting board. Using sharp kitchen shears, cut along one side of the backbone. Then, cut along the other side of the breast to completely remove the backbone. Set aside.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Turn the turkey over and press down hard with both hands onto the center of the breastbone until you hear and feel the bone crack.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Turn the turkey over. Using your index finger, gently press between the skin of the turkey and the meat. Wiggle your finger from side to side and cut away extra fat as needed. Do not tear the skin. Be sure to push your fingers down to separate the skin from the thigh and drumstick.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Spoon some of the spice rub under the skin and distribute evenly over the turkey. Turn the turkey over, and repeat underneath. Distribute remaining spice rub onto the outside of the turkey.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Place the turkey on the baking rack. Bake until a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast reads 165°F.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Remove the turkey from the oven and carefully place on a heat-resistant surface. Tent with foil and let rest for 30 minutes.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 While turkey is resting, place baking sheet (without wire rack) onto your stovetop. This will cover two burners.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Turn heat to medium high. Add brandy and scrape off all the bits on the bottom of the baking sheet. Turn off the heat, and pour into a fat separator.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 In a small bowl, whisk together 1/4 cup of the turkey or chicken broth with cornstarch. Set aside.
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 In a small saucepan over medium heat, whisk together broth and brandy sauce from the fat separator (minus the fat).
c2837fb4-9b28-4bed-9f22-4e13bdab2044 Whisk in cornstarch mixture, salt and pepper. Whisk constantly until gravy has thickened slightly. Be sure to add any drippings from the cutting board into the gravy.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Preheat the oven to 500°F. In a roasting pan, toss the melted butter, whole garlic cloves, butternut squash, apples, and onions together. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Mix together the room temperature butter, thyme, rosemary, orange zest, and minced garlic in a bowl. Place about 1/4 cup of salt and 2 tsps pepper in two small bowls. Get a piece of kitchen twine ready to tie the legs together. Place all of this close to the roasting pan, so you won't get turkey juices everywhere during the prep.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Remove the turkey from the bag. Locate and set aside neck and giblets package from inside the turkey cavity. Place the turkey on top of the vegetables. Cut a small slit in the skin above the cavity and gently work your hand between the skin and the breast meat. Spread the butter mixture under the skin, then rub it all over the breast, legs, thighs, and cavity of the bird. Sprinkle with Kosher salt. You probably won't need the entire 1/4 cup, but it should look like a light snow has fallen on the turkey. Follow that up with a sprinkling of pepper.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Stuff the cavity with the orange halves and a few onion and apple slices from the pan. Tie the legs together with kitchen twine and tuck the wing tips under the bird to protect them.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Place the turkey in the oven uncovered for 30 minutes, or until it is golden brown. Remove the turkey from the oven and lower the temperature to 350°F. Pour the chicken broth, hard cider, and apple cider into the pan, scraping up any bits at the bottom. Cover the breast meat with a small strip of parchment paper. Wrap the pan in foil. Place an oven safe or probe thermometer in the thickest part of the breast meat then return to the oven and continue to roast for 2-2.5 hours or until turkey reaches about 160°F. At that point, remove the foil and continue to roast until the thickest part of the breast reaches 165°F. Remove the turkey from the oven, tent with foil, and let rest for about 30 minutes prior to carving.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 To make the gravy, strain the vegetables, reserving them and the liquid for another use. Skim the fat off the top of the liquid. You can use a gravy separator or place it in the fridge for a bit to make this process easier.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Place 1/4 cup of the fat in a pot over medium heat. If you weren't able to get a full 1/4 cup of fat, add enough butter to make 1/4 cup. Measure out 1/2 cup of the reserved liquid from the roasting pan and whisk it together with the cornstarch to form a slurry. Stir this into the fat in the pan, whisking until the mixture begins to thicken. Slowly stir in the broth and then the cider in a steady stream, alternating stirring and whisking.
865c0f5a-378c-4bc0-97de-749ee1da9975 Continue to cook for another 5 or so minutes, or until the gravy is the consistency that you want. If desired, whisk in mustard and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve the turkey with the gravy.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Preheat the oven to 325°F. Lightly coat the rack of a roasting pan with non-stick spray and set aside.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Remove the giblets and the neck from the turkey cavity, set aside, and pat the turkey dry with a paper towel. Place the turkey, breast side up, on the roasting pan.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb In a small bowl, combine the thyme, oregano, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, chipotle chili powder, salt, pepper, and Truvia Brown Sugar Blend. Combine the seasoning mixture (reserving 1 tablespoon, set aside) with softened butter.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Cut a pocket between the skin and the breast meat. Work the butter mixture in the pocket, working it in between the legs and wings as best you can.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Drizzle melted butter over the outside of the turkey and sprinkle remaining seasoning mixture over butter. Spread this over the outside of the entire turkey.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Place chopped green pepper, onion, celery and garlic inside the turkey cavity. Pour chicken broth into the bottom of the pan.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Tent a sheet of aluminum foil over the turkey and place the turkey in the oven. Keep turkey loosely covered during the cooking time. Turkey should take 4-4.5 hours or until a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast reads 165°F.
b2b26052-2c1c-4880-bce4-2cc7c67a61eb Remove turkey and allow it to rest for 20 minutes before carving.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Preheat oven to 375°F.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Remove turkey from packaging.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Locate and set aside neck and giblets package from inside the turkey cavity.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Rinse turkey with cold water and completely pat dry with paper towels.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Place the turkey on a rack set in a large roasting pan. Tuck the wing tips under the turkey body. Place the giblets and half of the onions in the pan.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Fill turkey cavity with remaining onion, apple, jalapeno, garlic, carrots, celery and herbs.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 In a bowl, combine fig preserves, butter, oregano and paprika.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Rub half of the fig mixture all over the turkey, working some of it between the breast and the skin. Season the turkey generously with salt and pepper.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Add 2 cups broth to the roasting pan and roast turkey, basting every 30 minutes with drippings, for 1 hr.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Continue roasting the turkey until a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast registers 165°F, about 1-1.5 hours longer.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Cover the turkey loosely with foil if it begins to brown.
9b4c20d5-ef8a-4491-b0b3-968227c07635 Transfer to platter and brush with remaining fig mixture. Let rest for at least 20 minutes before carving.
91982eed-3e39-4b88-91f6-5708cc8a142a In a small bowl, combine the garlic, mustard, herbs, salt, pepper, olive oil and lemon juice to make a paste. Loosen the skin from the meat gently with your fingers and smear half of the paste directly on the meat. Spread the remaining paste evenly on the skin. Pour the wine into the bottom of your slow cooker.
91982eed-3e39-4b88-91f6-5708cc8a142a Place the turkey carefully over the wine and cook on LOW for 5-7 hours. Turkey is done when a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast reaches 165°F.
91982eed-3e39-4b88-91f6-5708cc8a142a Once the turkey is done, remove and put in an oven-safe dish, unless your slow cooker is oven safe. Broil for 3-5 minutes, watching the turkey carefully to make sure not to burn the skin.
91982eed-3e39-4b88-91f6-5708cc8a142a When the turkey is nicely browned, cover with foil and allow it to rest at room temperature for 15 minutes. Slice and serve with the pan juices spooned over the turkey.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Remove the neck and giblet package from the turkey cavity, set aside, and free the legs from the clamp.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Wash the turkey and dry with paper towels. Let sit in a cool place while you prepare the injection butter.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Roughly chop the seeded jalapeño pepper. Place 1/2 cup basil, chopped jalapeño pepper, salted butter, 1 TB salt, and 1/2 TB black pepper in a small pot and simmer for five minutes until butter is melted.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Let cool for 5 minutes. Strain or ladle large pieces out of cooled butter sauce. Pour into a cup for ease of injection.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Using an injection needle, inject liquid into the turkey throughout the breast and thighs, avoid making too many holes. Try getting three different injection angles out of the same needle hole.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Once injected, the turkey can marinate for several hours to overnight in the fridge before grilling. If any injection liquid oozes out, you can rub it gently over the turkey.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Preheat the grill to 425°F. Cooking time will vary based on the size of bird.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Baste the turkey with vegetable oil and flip. Season with herbed poultry blend on top of the bird and flip to get to the bottom of the turkey.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Add 1/2 cup fresh basil, 1 lemon sliced in half, and 1 onion sliced in half to the turkey cavity.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 Line the grill with a grill liner. Place the turkey on the liner in the grill for the amount of cooking time based on the weight of the bird.
2e33a970-7c08-4199-8134-2025d6b4a668 The turkey is ready to eat once a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast reads 165°F. Remove from the grill and let sit before carving, 15-20 minutes.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Preheat oven to 400°F and remove puff pastry from freezer to thaw.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 In a medium bowl, mix cranberry sauce, apples and cinnamon. Set aside.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Cook bacon over medium-high heat in a large pan. Remove cooked bacon, set aside to cool.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 In the same pan, heat olive oil and add garlic. Stir for a few minutes.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Stir in rosemary, thyme and crumbled bacon then turn off the heat.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Add the ground turkey to pan, sprinkle with salt, chipotle pepper and stir all ingredients together. Cook until ground turkey is lightly browned.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Slice the cheese.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 On a parchment lined baking sheet, roll out a puff pastry.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Spoon half of the turkey mixture in the middle of the puff pastry. Form into a rectangular loaf.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Cover the loaf with several slices of cheese.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Cover the cheese with 2-3 spoonfuls of the cranberry and apple sauce.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Cut strips along the edges of the dough. Make as many cuts along the sides as you want, just make sure to have the same amount on each side.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 After cutting 6-8 strips of dough on the sides, you are ready to braid.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Fold the top and the bottom ends over the turkey, then cross the side strips over each other to make the braid.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Repeat with the second puff pastry.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Make an egg wash with one beaten egg and a splash of cool water.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Brush each pastry with the egg wash.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Bake for 25-30 minutes until the braid is golden brown.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Use a food thermometer to make sure the turkey is 165°F before eating.
33c60196-82ab-4aac-aa5e-a5a6da5c4012 Let set for at least 5 minutes, then slice and serve.
097d03b5-44e7-4608-80e3-316d1c340861 Prepare the sliders. Divide the ground turkey into 8 equal balls. Shape each ball into a patty approximately 3" across or about the size of the slider buns. Cover and refrigerate until needed.
097d03b5-44e7-4608-80e3-316d1c340861 Prepare the red curry mayonnaise. Combine the mayonnaise and Thai red curry paste in a small bowl. Using a rubber spatula or whisk, stir well until combined.
097d03b5-44e7-4608-80e3-316d1c340861 Season the sliders with salt and pepper as desired. On a grill or in a sauté pan, cook over medium heat for 5-8 minutes or until an internal temperature of 165°F is reached on a meat thermometer.
097d03b5-44e7-4608-80e3-316d1c340861 As the patties cook, spread the red curry mayonnaise on the tops of the slider buns. Place the pickles on the bottom half of buns.
097d03b5-44e7-4608-80e3-316d1c340861 When the sliders are cooked, remove from heat and place on the bottom buns. Drizzle the Thai sweet chili sauce on top of the patties and add the bun tops.
a034bfba-13bb-499f-afa3-389cb8371297 Preheat oven to 325°F. Locate and set aside neck and giblets package from inside the turkey cavity. Unwrap the turkey in the sink and pat dry with paper towels.
a034bfba-13bb-499f-afa3-389cb8371297 Coat the outside of the turkey with butter, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and place on a rack in a large roasting pan and roast for 1 hour.
a034bfba-13bb-499f-afa3-389cb8371297 Combine the chicken broth, pomegranate juice and maple syrup in a nonstick skillet and bring to a simmer over low heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until reduced to about 1/3 cup, about 30 minutes.
a034bfba-13bb-499f-afa3-389cb8371297 After 1 hour of roasting, begin basting with the glaze. If the bird gets too dark, cover loosely with foil. Continue roasting until a thermometer inserted into the breast reaches 170°F.
a034bfba-13bb-499f-afa3-389cb8371297 Transfer the turkey to a platter, tent with foil and let rest 30 minutes before slicing.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a Preheat oven to 350°F. Pat the turkey breast roast dry with paper towels and place on a roasting rack in a roasting pan.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a In a small bowl, combine the paprika, salt, brown sugar, onion powder and dry mustard. Spread the spice rub on the turkey on all sides.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a Transfer turkey to the oven and cook until the internal temperature reaches 165° F on an instant-read thermometer. Let the turkey rest 20 minutes before slicing.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a Pulse cauliflower in a food processor until it's riced.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat and spray with cooking spray. Add the cauliflower and gently toast, stirring occasionally, until it starts to brown in a few spots, about 5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a In the same skillet, toast the nuts and spices over low heat. When fragrant, about a minute, add to the cauliflower. Stir in the currants and lemon juice and stir to combine.
1117fe71-d36d-4dfd-82ae-8ac61ba1957a Serve slices of turkey fanned out on top of the cauliflower couscous.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f In a bowl, combine salt, pepper, garlic powder and flour.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Dredge turkey in flour mixture.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f In a large frying pan over medium heat, quickly brown turkey in melted butter, turning once.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Add 1/4 cup Marsala wine or chicken broth (reserve 1/4 cup for pan sauce).
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Cook on high for 1 minute.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Remove turkey from pan and keep warm.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Pour remaining wine or broth and chicken broth into pan. Scrape loose all the brown particles and bring to a boil. Add mushrooms and boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Pour demi-glaze over scallopini.
5a37c4ad-1ea2-421f-99e9-6173c4b3653f Serve over angel hair pasta, egg noodles or fettuccine (optional).
afa2f2fe-03f2-4307-b618-d8f046e81991 Preheat oven to 375°F. Line a baking dish with foil.
afa2f2fe-03f2-4307-b618-d8f046e81991 Heat a large nonstick skillet and spray with cooking spray. Add the spinach and cook just until wilted. Combine the spinach and goat cheese in a small bowl and season lightly with pepper.
afa2f2fe-03f2-4307-b618-d8f046e81991 Place the turkey on a work surface and divide the spinach and cheese mixture; spread evenly across each slice. Spread the filling about 3/4 of the way across the turkey. Roll the scallopini starting with the filling end and ending with the unfilled end. Secure each roll with a wooden toothpick to hold it together.
afa2f2fe-03f2-4307-b618-d8f046e81991 In small bowl, combine oil, paprika and salt; gently roll the scallopini rolls in the mixture to coat. At this point, rolls can be wrapped in plastic wrap and refrigerated for up to 24 hours.
afa2f2fe-03f2-4307-b618-d8f046e81991 Place rolls on the prepared pan and roast until turkey reaches 165° F, about 20 minutes.
afa2f2fe-03f2-4307-b618-d8f046e81991 When cool enough to handle remove and discard toothpicks; slice crosswise into 3/4-inch slices to serve. Pierce with toothpick, garnish with cucumber and arugula.
68314f93-7794-45c4-861a-40160ccb5315 Roast turkey according to package instructions and an instant-read thermometer registers 165°F when inserted into the thickest part of the breast. Cover the breast loosely with aluminum foil if necessary to prevent overbrowning. Let cool and slice 1 pound of turkey into thin slices.
68314f93-7794-45c4-861a-40160ccb5315 Combine the yogurt, mayonnaise, honey, lime juice, lime zest and sriracha sauce in a small bowl.
68314f93-7794-45c4-861a-40160ccb5315 Spread each slice of bread with sriracha honey lime sauce.
68314f93-7794-45c4-861a-40160ccb5315 Top each slice of bread with arugula greens, cucumber slices and the turkey. Serve open-faced.
f6a7825d-7aa4-4470-81a6-c3d4874dc54a Place breast cutlets on bottom of large 13 x 9-inch baking dish and cover with mushrooms.
f6a7825d-7aa4-4470-81a6-c3d4874dc54a Mix remaining ingredients in a medium bowl until smooth. Pour sauce over turkey and mushrooms.
f6a7825d-7aa4-4470-81a6-c3d4874dc54a Bake at 350°F, uncovered, for 35 minutes (do not open oven). Cook turkey to 165°F using a meat thermometer.
f6a7825d-7aa4-4470-81a6-c3d4874dc54a Remove turkey from dish, reserving sauce.
f6a7825d-7aa4-4470-81a6-c3d4874dc54a Slice turkey. Place on a bed of your favorite cooked pasta, rice or egg noodles.
f6a7825d-7aa4-4470-81a6-c3d4874dc54a Drizzle with sour cream sauce and mushrooms. Garnish with chives and black pepper.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Heat nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Add turkey, onion, garlic and mushroom to skillet.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Sauté until turkey has reached a temperature of 165°F as measured by a meat thermometer.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Add flour, salt and pepper.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Cook uncovered 5 minutes.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Add soup and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
1dc07e70-4be3-40c8-b5f5-d91532e4757e Serve over buttered egg noodles or pappardelle. Garnish with parsley and black pepper.
afb8f154-496d-445c-9262-552336374901 Place tomatillos and green chiles in blender and blend until smooth. Add to an oval 4- to 6-quart slow cooker.
afb8f154-496d-445c-9262-552336374901 Add the cumin, salt, pepper, broth, onions and garlic, and stir. Then add the turkey and make sure it's completely coated in liquid. Cover; cook turkey to 165°F using a meat thermometer, about 4 hours on high or about 6 hours on low.
afb8f154-496d-445c-9262-552336374901 Remove the turkey from the soup and let cool. Shred the meat and return to soup; discard the bone.
afb8f154-496d-445c-9262-552336374901 Stir hominy into slow cooker. Cover; cook on high for 1 hour longer. Season to taste with salt.
afb8f154-496d-445c-9262-552336374901 Top individual servings with avocado, cilantro, cabbage and radish slices, and serve each bowl with a wedge of lime.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Cook polenta according to package instructions.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc When polenta is cooked, take it off the heat and add thyme, pepper, fontina and olive oil, and stir until melted and very creamy; keep warm.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Heat a large, preferably nonstick, skillet and coat with cooking spray.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Place the sausages in skillet and cook over medium-high heat, until brown on each side, about 5 minutes per side, then add 1/4 cup of water and cover, turning heat to medium-low. Cook for another 5 minutes.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Take sausages out of pan and place on a cutting board to cool. When cool, cut sausages into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Pour liquid out of the skillet, then add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil, onions and peppers; cook over medium-high heat until softened, about 7 minutes.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Add the sliced sausages and garlic to the pan; stir and cook for 2 minutes.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Deglaze the pan with wine and simmer until liquid is reduced to just a few tablespoons.
8d254b2b-b6c0-4575-a77f-9365a58e9afc Spoon polenta onto plates, top with the sausage mixture, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Heat a large, preferably nonstick, Dutch oven on medium heat until hot and coat with cooking spray.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Add sausages and cook until well browned, about 10 minutes, turning frequently. Transfer sausages to plate, and when cool enough to handle cut sausages into 1/2-inch thick diagonal slices. Note that the sausages will not be completely cooked.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Add the onion to the Dutch oven and cook, stirring often, until soft, about 3 minutes.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Add garlic and Cajun seasoning and stir, just until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Add vegetable oil and flour and cook, stirring until the flour begins to brown, about 2 minutes.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Add tomatoes and broth, increase heat to high and bring to a boil.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Add the sausage and okra to the pot and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook until the okra is heated through and sausage is cooked, about 5 minutes.
d5341b88-9099-4c6c-96f8-4414820c0a44 Serve the stew in bowls over rice with green onions on top and French bread on the side.
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d Heat a large, preferably nonstick, Dutch oven over medium-high heat; coat with cooking spray.
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d Add onions to the Dutch oven and cook over medium-high heat until softened, about 3 minutes
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d Add the sausage and crumble, cooking until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d Add the chicken broth, tomatoes, chickpeas and Italian seasoning.
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d Add the spinach and cook just until it wilts. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
4507b34a-78db-4ebf-991c-4d56b2cdc19d To serve, place grilled bread in bowls, pour the stew on top and sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.
a58c8ae6-807c-4cc9-a170-0d87316af065 Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook pasta according to the package directions, but 2 minutes before the pasta is done (the very center of the pasta should still be raw) add the broccoli rabe and continue cooking. Drain and set aside.
a58c8ae6-807c-4cc9-a170-0d87316af065 Return the pot to the stove over medium heat; add the oil. Add the sausage and cook until no longer pink, breaking it up as it browns, about 3 minutes.
a58c8ae6-807c-4cc9-a170-0d87316af065 Add the onion to the sausage and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.
a58c8ae6-807c-4cc9-a170-0d87316af065 Add the garlic and crushed red pepper. Cook until the garlic is fragrant, about 30 seconds.
a58c8ae6-807c-4cc9-a170-0d87316af065 Add the chicken broth and bring to a simmer and stir in black pepper.
a58c8ae6-807c-4cc9-a170-0d87316af065 Add the drained pasta and broccoli rabe to the sausage onion sauce and toss until the pasta is coated in the sauce. Serve with Parmesan cheese.
f502a01f-13d7-45ab-97c3-59881785e715 Cook noodles according to package instructions until al dente. Drain well.
f502a01f-13d7-45ab-97c3-59881785e715 Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add oil. Stir in ginger and garlic and cook just until fragrant, about 15 seconds.
f502a01f-13d7-45ab-97c3-59881785e715 Add turkey and cook to 165°F using a meat thermometer, stirring occasionally and breaking up turkey with a wooden spoon until browned, about 5 minutes.
f502a01f-13d7-45ab-97c3-59881785e715 Whisk broth, peanut butter, vinegar, soy sauce, sherry, sugar and crushed pepper in medium bowl. Pour into skillet and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer, stirring occasionally until liquid thickens and reduces by about half, about 10 minutes.
f502a01f-13d7-45ab-97c3-59881785e715 Top noodles with sauce, green onions and cucumber strips.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, Dijon mustard, salt and pepper.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Add bread, pushing it into the mixture so it absorbs it. Set aside, tossing once in a while so the bread absorbs the mixture evenly.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Heat large nonstick skillet over medium heat and add the oil.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Add breakfast sausage and cook, breaking it apart and crumbling it, until no longer pink, about 3 minutes.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Add the diced onion and peppers and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, 3 to 5 minutes.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Take off the heat and let sit until warm but not hot, about 15 minutes. Add to the bread and egg mixture.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Coat 6 ramekins or small baking dishes with cooking spray. Pour in bread-sausage-egg mixture. Sprinkle with the cheese. Cover the dish securely with plastic wrap and refrigerate it overnight, or for about 8 hours.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Remove the strata from the fridge 30 minutes before putting it in the oven to take the chill off. Preheat the oven to 350°F and bake uncovered until the eggs are fully cooked, about 30 minutes.
435c10d8-a4fc-403a-8265-e9c5b7198950 Let the strata rest for 5 minutes before slicing and serving. Garnish with chives.
862216e9-3f71-441c-b946-491fb858b1b3 Heat a large saucepan over medium heat and add 1 tablespoon oil. Add carrot, celery, onion and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion softens, about 3 minutes.
862216e9-3f71-441c-b946-491fb858b1b3 Add ground turkey and cook, stirring occasionally and breaking up meat with a wooden spoon, cook to 165°F using a meat thermometer, about 4 minutes.
862216e9-3f71-441c-b946-491fb858b1b3 Transfer the mixture to a 4- to 6-quart slow cooker. Add the tomatoes with their puree, 1/3 cup water, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, 1 teaspoon salt, crushed red pepper and bay leaf. Stir well. Cover and cook for 3 hours on high or 6 hours on low.
862216e9-3f71-441c-b946-491fb858b1b3 Using a spiral cutter, mandoline or large holes on a box grater, cut zucchini into long thin noodles; stop grating when you reach the seedy center.
862216e9-3f71-441c-b946-491fb858b1b3 Heat the remaining tablespoon oil in a very large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the zucchini and cook, tossing often with two spoons, just until the zucchini is heated through and beginning to soften, about 3 minutes. Do not overcook. Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
862216e9-3f71-441c-b946-491fb858b1b3 Transfer zucchini to bowls. Top each with sauce and serve with Parmesan cheese.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until soft but not brown, about 3 minutes.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Add peas, water and salt, and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover skillet and simmer just until tender, about 3 minutes. Stir in the lemon zest and set aside.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Sprinkle the flour on a large plate and season with salt and pepper.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Dredge turkey in flour. Shake off the excess flour. Set aside.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 In a large skillet over medium heat, heat olive oil and a teaspoon of butter. Once hot, add the turkey and cook, browning on each side, about 2 minutes total. Remove to a clean plate.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Cook turkey in batches, adding more butter as necessary.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Once all turkey is cooked, lower the heat and add wine and lemon slices to the skillet. Deglaze the pan and simmer until slightly reduced, about 2 minutes. Add any remaining butter and the turkey, coating each piece with the pan sauce.
a14edf65-6c2f-4246-9a4e-84ae540bb519 Place turkey on a clean platter, sprinkle with parsley, season to taste with pepper, and serve with peas and roast potatoes. Garnish with capers if desired.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 Combine the mustard, vinegar, olive oil and honey in a bowl and mix until smooth. Set aside about 1/3 of the sauce for basting.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 Place sausages in a pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil then gently simmer for 10 minutes.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 When cool enough to handle, cut each sausage into 7 chunks of equal size.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 Microwave potatoes for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 When potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut them into 1-inch pieces and toss them along with the peppers and sausages in the mustard glaze in a large bowl.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 Thread potatoes, red pepper and sausage chunks onto 8 skewers.
04c63efc-bdec-4ca2-bb5a-2f9b5bbe4fc4 Place skewers on a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat; brush with the reserved mustard mixture. Grill and turn until sausages are completely cooked and reach internal temperature of 165¬ F and red peppers are cooked, about 10 minutes. Season to taste with pepper. Garnish with frisée, if desired.
8c84f0df-7403-4a59-81ab-1a92f85b7aaa Preheat oven to 450°F.
8c84f0df-7403-4a59-81ab-1a92f85b7aaa Spread pesto evenly over pizza crust. Top with an even layer of mozzarella cheese followed by the meatballs.
8c84f0df-7403-4a59-81ab-1a92f85b7aaa Bake on bottom rack of oven, 8-10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
b0d8bfd9-0184-49ed-b16c-b92d28346b14 Toast buns under broiler, 1 minute.
b0d8bfd9-0184-49ed-b16c-b92d28346b14 Microwave meatballs in a microwave-safe dish, 2-4 minutes or until heated through.
b0d8bfd9-0184-49ed-b16c-b92d28346b14 Place roasted pepper on each bottom bun and top with meatball followed by provolone.
b0d8bfd9-0184-49ed-b16c-b92d28346b14 Broil, 1 minute or until bubbly.
b0d8bfd9-0184-49ed-b16c-b92d28346b14 Add a few leaves of arugula and close slider with top bun.
7acacd26-20df-4708-bd24-2db2c224f1e5 Add carrots, celery, onion, potato, chicken broth, salt and thyme to a 4- to 6-quart oval slow cooker.
7acacd26-20df-4708-bd24-2db2c224f1e5 Cover and cook on low-heat setting about 3 hours or on high setting about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
7acacd26-20df-4708-bd24-2db2c224f1e5 Stir in corn, milk and turkey. Cover and cook about 1 hour on high or until turkey is cooked to 165°F using a meat thermometer.
