7acacd26-20df-4708-bd24-2db2c224f1e5 In a small bowl stir together cornstarch and water; stir into the chowder mixture. Cover and cook until chowder begins to bubble and thickens slightly, about 10-15 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Garnish with parsley, if desired, and serve with breadsticks.
df218830-b475-4914-a37c-3021e4f8bfaa Preheat lightly oiled grill to 500°F - 600°F.
df218830-b475-4914-a37c-3021e4f8bfaa In small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise and mustard.
df218830-b475-4914-a37c-3021e4f8bfaa Season turkey patties with salt and pepper.
df218830-b475-4914-a37c-3021e4f8bfaa Place patties on grill and cook for 4-5 minutes per side until cooked through and a meat thermometer reads 165°F throughout the patty.
df218830-b475-4914-a37c-3021e4f8bfaa Spread mayonnaise mixture on cut sides of buns.
df218830-b475-4914-a37c-3021e4f8bfaa Place turkey patties in buns and top each patty with 1 lettuce leaf, 1 tomato slice and 2 bacon strips.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Tip: If using Honeysuckle White HomeStyle Turkey Meatloaf, skip to step 9.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray a 9×5 loaf pan with food release spray and then line with aluminum foil.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Heat oil in a sauté pan until shimmering. Add the onions and sauté over medium heat for 4-5 minutes, or until softened.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Add the garlic and sauté for 1 minute.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Add the mushrooms, salt, and pepper. Increase heat to high and sauté mushrooms, stirring frequently for about 5 minutes or until done.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Transfer the onions and mushrooms to a large bowl.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Combine the panko breadcrumbs and milk in a small bowl. Add the eggs and stir well to combine.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Add the breadcrumb-egg mixture to the sautéed mushrooms, and then add the ground turkey.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Using a rubber spatula or your hand, gently mix all ingredients until combined. Do not over mix.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Scrape the meatloaf mixture into the foil-lined pan and smooth the top.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Brush about 1/8 cup of thai chili sauce evenly over the meatloaf. Cover with a layer of aluminum foil.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Bake for 40 minutes, then remove foil.
c8ea446b-1b2c-4a95-859e-b2a0714bcc82 Continue baking 5-10 more minutes. Turkey is fully cooked when meat reaches an internal temperature of 165°F using a meat thermometer.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Preheat oven to 375°F.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Cook turkey to 165°F using a meat thermometer, about 10 minutes.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f In a small bowl, mix sour cream and ranch dressing.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f In a medium bowl, combine 1 cup sour cream mixture and turkey.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Divide turkey mixture, cheese and salsa evenly over tortillas.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Roll up and place seam-side down in a greased 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Bake, uncovered, for 25-30 minutes.
6759fb72-fec5-4e55-9a42-18091414bd4f Top with tomato, green onion and any remaining salsa and/or sour cream mixture.
7ed8be25-7a53-4422-9b0b-65de247c0cc8 To make spicy cranberry sauce, place ingredients in medium saucepan. Boil 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cranberries burst and sauce is thickened; refrigerate.
7ed8be25-7a53-4422-9b0b-65de247c0cc8 Sauté cutlets in lightly oiled skillet over medium heat approximately 5 minutes per side or until turkey is no longer pink in the center and reaches internal temperature of 170°F.
7ed8be25-7a53-4422-9b0b-65de247c0cc8 Cool and cut into strips.
7ed8be25-7a53-4422-9b0b-65de247c0cc8 Spread 2 tablespoons cheese over tortillas to 1/2 inch from edge.
7ed8be25-7a53-4422-9b0b-65de247c0cc8 Layer lettuce, 1/2 cup turkey, 1/4 cup spicy cranberry sauce, 1/2 teaspoon cilantro and several apple slices. Repeat three times. Fold tortilla bottom and top over filling, then fold one side to center. Fold last side to overlap center and roll tight.
3206aeea-46b3-4062-be65-74fd6bb39b35 Preheat the oven to 450°F and line a rimmed baking sheet with foil.
3206aeea-46b3-4062-be65-74fd6bb39b35 Put the Brussels sprouts on the baking sheet, drizzle with a tablespoon of olive oil and sprinkle with salt. Transfer to the oven and roast until tender, about 25 minutes.
3206aeea-46b3-4062-be65-74fd6bb39b35 In a large skillet over medium heat, add a tablespoon of olive oil and bacon and cook, stirring frequently, until the bacon is well browned, 8-10 minutes. Remove the bacon, drain on paper towels and crumble or roughly chop.
3206aeea-46b3-4062-be65-74fd6bb39b35 Add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil and vinegar to the skillet (the vinegar will sizzle immediately), scraping up any browned bits in the pan.
3206aeea-46b3-4062-be65-74fd6bb39b35 Take off the heat and whisk in the honey and mustard. Set aside.
3206aeea-46b3-4062-be65-74fd6bb39b35 Transfer sprouts to a serving dish and drizzle with the dressing. Sprinkle with the bacon. Serve immediately.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 In a mixing bowl, whisk together the garlic, yogurt, cucumber, dill, lemon juice, salt and pepper, and mix in the cucumber and dill. Refrigerate until serving.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Combine boiling water and bulgur in a medium bowl. Let stand until bulgur is tender, about 15 minutes.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Drain in a fine mesh strainer and cool completely. Squeeze any excess liquid from bulgur.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 In a food processor combine the garlic, bulgur, onion, parsley, yogurt, cumin, paprika, salt and pepper, and pulse until the onion is minced.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Add turkey and process, stopping occasionally to stir, until well combined. (Or mince onion, parsley and garlic by hand, and stir ingredients together in a large bowl.)
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Drain soaked skewers. Divide turkey mixture equally into 12 sausage-shaped kofta, each about 4 inches long and 1 inch wide. Thread each onto a skewer and brush with oil.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Preheat grill for direct cooking over medium heat (about 400° F). Lightly oil grill grate.
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Place kofta on grill, perpendicular to grate. Cook, with lid closed, turning once or twice with a thin metal spatula, until firm when pressed, 10 to 12 minutes. To discourage burned skewers, slip a strip of aluminum foil under exposed skewer handles. (The kofta can also be cooked in a broiler for 10 to 12 minutes. To keep the handles from burning, wrap each in a small strip of aluminum foil.)
1dccffb2-09ff-4b20-bbc4-28000a75c524 Remove kofta from grill and serve with tzatziki sauce and thinly sliced vegetables in pita.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Preheat the oven to 350°F.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 In a small bowl, combine the miso and honey to make a thick paste.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Place turkey on a roasting rack in a roasting pan and rub the surface with the miso mixture, using just enough to coat it.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Roast the turkey according to package instructions, until an instant-read thermometer registers 165° F when inserted into the thickest part of the breast. Cover the breast loosely with aluminum foil if necessary to prevent overbrowning.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Let roast rest 15 minutes, then slice 8 thin slices for the soup.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Whisk together the chicken broth, gravy, miso and soy sauce in a saucepan. Heat gently over medium-low heat until very hot.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Cook noodles in a large pot of boiling water according to package directions until al dente; drain.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Divide noodles among bowls. Top each bowl with 2 overlapping slices of turkey, placing it off to one side. Ladle broth over turkey and noodles.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Cut the eggs in half lengthwise and place a half, yolk side up, on top of noodles in each bowl.
1cb94fc3-2c54-43f1-a884-a66be6774039 Garnish each bowl with a pile of green onions.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Preheat oven to 350°F. Place sausages on a greased sheet pan.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Roast sausages for 12-15 minutes, or until an internal temperature of 165° F is reached.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Remove cooked sausages from oven and reserve.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Make the tomato sauce. Heat the olive oil in a 4-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Add onions and garlic and stir constantly until onions are soft and garlic is light gold, about 5 minutes.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Add the crushed tomatoes to the sautéed onions and garlic. Bring sauce to a boil, and then reduce heat to low and simmer while you cut the sausages.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 When sausages are cool enough to handle, cut on the bias into 1/2-inch thick slices.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Add sausages to tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Season to taste with salt and pepper.
e25d9990-f102-49ea-a1a7-279d22db4d62 Ladle sauce over hot rigatoni. Serve with shaved Parmesan.
4edac0f7-4a29-4cb2-9fc8-090939605527 Cut each turkey thigh into three pieces.
4edac0f7-4a29-4cb2-9fc8-090939605527 Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
4edac0f7-4a29-4cb2-9fc8-090939605527 Cook turkey until no longer pink, about 2 to 3 minutes per side for each piece.
4edac0f7-4a29-4cb2-9fc8-090939605527 Combine tomatoes, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper; mix well.
4edac0f7-4a29-4cb2-9fc8-090939605527 Spoon over turkey. Reduce heat; simmer partially covered for 25 to 30 minutes.
4edac0f7-4a29-4cb2-9fc8-090939605527 Add mushrooms, zucchini, yellow squash and onion. Continue simmering partially covered for 7 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp and turkey is fork-tender.
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 In small bowl, combine cumin, salt, black pepper, cinnamon and cayenne pepper; rub turkey with spice mixture.
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 In a large-size slow cooker, combine garbanzos, tomatoes, onion, carrots and ginger; place turkey on top.
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 Cook on HIGH 3 to 4 hours or until a thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the breast registers 165°F.
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 Remove skin and slice turkey.
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 Arrange turkey on a serving platter; spoon vegetables and sauce on top
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 Sprinkle with cilantro.
db9d4004-c87f-44d3-88d1-d8459b66e293 Serve with couscous mixed with cilantro (optional).
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Heat oven to 350°F.
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Whisk together apricot jam, orange juice and ginger.
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Season turkey with salt and pepper; brush with apricot jam mixture.
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Roast about 30 minutes, basting occasionally with pan juices, until internal temperature reaches 170°F.
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Transfer turkey to platter; keep warm.
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Pour pan juices into skillet over medium heat, add apricots and simmer until apricots are warm.
58818172-de3f-41c3-819b-643ebe1674a4 Spoon sauce and apricots over turkey. Serve with asparagus roasted with olive oil and salt and pepper (optional).
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Preheat charcoal or gas grill.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Cook onion and mushroom until softened, about 5 minutes.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Wrap each tenderloin with 3 strips of bacon; secure with toothpick.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Grill turkey for 5 minutes on each side.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Cover and grill for 10 more minutes or until no longer pink and internal temperature reaches 165°F.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Remove turkey; top with onions, mushrooms and cheese.
f603c834-f8c4-45d8-a01d-a946740ca970 Garnish with parsley.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Heat oven to 350°F.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Pat the turkey breast dry with paper towels and place on a rack in the roasting pan.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 In a small bowl combine the olive oil, lemon juice, sage, parsley, lemon zest and salt.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Slide a few whole sage leaves under the skin of the roast and rub the top and sides of the turkey breast with the herb mixture.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Roast for 30 minutes, then add the lemon slices to the roasting pan.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Continue roasting about another 20 minutes or until juices run clear and a meat thermometer reads 165° F.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Let stand for 10-15 minutes before slicing.
f1bb138b-9636-4fe5-9b21-192b83475a31 Garnish with thyme sprigs, if desired.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e In a large sauté pan, brown turkey sausage over medium-high heat until no pink remains.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Add butter to the pan and melt.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Add diced onion and sauté until softened, about 3-4 minutes. Add minced garlic and sauté 30-45 seconds. Do not brown garlic.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Stir in flour. Reduce heat to medium and cook the roux for 4-5 minutes.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Using a wire whisk, slowly stir in milk, half and half, kosher salt and black pepper.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Stir constantly until gravy has thickened.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Remove from heat. Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco to taste. Adjust seasoning.
4649928e-f477-41a8-a2ef-a07a54d05f0e Serve over hot thyme buttermilk biscuits.
ec60e203-a155-42b1-af0f-5938d46c6f41 Preheat oven to 400°F. In a medium bowl or resealable plastic bag combine the lime juice, oil and salt. Add the turkey cutlets and set aside for 5 minutes.
ec60e203-a155-42b1-af0f-5938d46c6f41 Lightly spray both sides of the tortillas with cooking spray and arrange them in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet. Lightly season the tortillas with salt and bake until crisp, about 10 minutes.
ec60e203-a155-42b1-af0f-5938d46c6f41 Meanwhile, heat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat. Remove the turkey from marinade, pat dry with paper towels and grill until browned and cooked through, about 5 minutes per side. Let rest until cool enough to handle, about 5 minutes; slice thinly or shred.
ec60e203-a155-42b1-af0f-5938d46c6f41 Heat the refried beans in a small nonstick saucepan over low heat or in the microwave in a microwave-safe bowl.
ec60e203-a155-42b1-af0f-5938d46c6f41 Spread each tortilla with refried beans, turkey and a tablespoon of salsa, top with avocado and lettuce, plus a dollop of sour cream, if you like.
2dffd4cb-7d7c-40e6-bfea-c667f96e6a6c Combine the onion, curry powder and ginger in a 4- to 6-quart oval slow cooker.
2dffd4cb-7d7c-40e6-bfea-c667f96e6a6c Stir in the chicken broth, coconut milk and the turkey wing. Cover and cook for 4 hours on low or 2 hours on high or until turkey is fork tender.
2dffd4cb-7d7c-40e6-bfea-c667f96e6a6c Remove the turkey wing from the broth. When cool enough to handle strip off the skin and discard. Pull the meat from the bones and shred into small pieces. Add the meat back to the slow cooker and discard the bones.
2dffd4cb-7d7c-40e6-bfea-c667f96e6a6c Break up the rice noodles and add them and the red pepper to the slow cooker. Cover and cook until noodles are cooked, about 20 minutes.
2dffd4cb-7d7c-40e6-bfea-c667f96e6a6c Season with soy sauce to taste. Serve each bowl of soup with bean sprouts, lime, cilantro and jalapeños.
def5c710-4681-467b-b216-dc2fd0ef429c Combine the onion, cranberry sauce, chicken broth, vinegar and salt in a 4- to 6-quart oval slow cooker.
def5c710-4681-467b-b216-dc2fd0ef429c Add the turkey drumsticks to the slow cooker and coat with the cranberry mixture.
def5c710-4681-467b-b216-dc2fd0ef429c Cover and cook until tender, about 4 hours on high, 6 hours on low.
def5c710-4681-467b-b216-dc2fd0ef429c Add the frozen cranberries and cook for another 15 minutes.
def5c710-4681-467b-b216-dc2fd0ef429c Combine the cornstarch and water and gently stir into the slow cooker. Cover and cook for an additional 10 minutes or until sauce bubbles and thickens.
def5c710-4681-467b-b216-dc2fd0ef429c Pull the meat from the bones. Serve with mashed potatoes and roasted Brussels sprouts (optional).
7b1091ae-1dd9-4bc3-b740-697aaed694b8 In large soup pot, heat oil over medium heat. Add turkey; cook to 165°F using a meat thermometer, stirring occasionally to break up turkey.
7b1091ae-1dd9-4bc3-b740-697aaed694b8 Add onion, flour and chili powder; cook about 5 minutes.
7b1091ae-1dd9-4bc3-b740-697aaed694b8 Add beans, chicken broth and chiles; bring to a simmer and cook, covered, about 30 minutes.
7b1091ae-1dd9-4bc3-b740-697aaed694b8 Stir in cilantro.
7b1091ae-1dd9-4bc3-b740-697aaed694b8 Serve with tortilla chips or warm corn tortillas and sour cream.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Preheat the oven to 350° F. Place the turkey breast on a rack in a roasting pan.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d In a small bowl, combine the garlic, mustard, salt, lemon zest, onion powder and lemon juice. Spread the paste evenly on the turkey.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Roast the turkey according to package instructions, until the skin is golden brown and an instant-read thermometer registers 165° F when inserted into the thickest part of the breast.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Allow the turkey to rest at room temperature for 10-15 minutes before slicing.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Place quinoa in a fine mesh sieve. Rinse thoroughly under cold water.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Add quinoa to a medium saucepan; add a pinch of salt and the water. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until water is completely absorbed, about 20 minutes.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Transfer quinoa to a medium bowl along with chickpeas, lemon zest, parsley, sun-dried tomatoes, green onions, lemon juice and olive oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
1c97e07b-c06a-409a-bd90-ec9abdb1d01d Serve slices of turkey over a bed of the quinoa.
